description:
As a data analyst, you collect, process, analyze and use data that comes through different channels. You extract, describe, analyze and interpret the data needed to make informed business decisions. You provide guidance and support to clients for analytics solution mandates that involve using data and designing reports adapted to business needs. You use your analytical skills and extensive knowledge of your line of business to work on complex business projects and initiatives using data from different databases. You prepare recommendations, solutions and action plans based on the organization's objectives and priorities. Your projects and initiatives require extensive knowledge of your field. You serve as a data use resource for various stakeholders. You interact with stakeholders working in other fields to understand needs, and present and explain analysis results. More specifically, you will be required to:
• Analyze and identify user needs, work on mandates to collect, process and analyze data, and ensure operationalization through cross-sector coordination

• Identify opportunities to improve work methods and processes, and recommend improvements to data management tools
• Help clients define their needs, make recommendations and provide advice for selecting, implementing and using data management tools
• Do research and perform descriptive and diagnostic analyses to ensure optimal data use and make recommendations in line with business issues and needs.

• A minimum of four years of relevant experience

• Knowledge of French is required

description:
Company Description

As a leading agriculture business, we are committed to supporting the families who help our business units thrive in California’s Central Valley. With a comprehensive strategy to combat preventable chronic illnesses, we partner with our communities to create a healthier future—and you could be part of this transformative team. Not only are we redefining health and wellness in California’s Central Valley, but we’re also offering these programs entirely free to our employees, their families, and the communities where they live and work.

Join our dedicated team to provide high-quality, patient-centered care and make a significant impact on the lives of employees at The Wonderful Company, who are the force behind beloved household names like Wonderful Pistachios®, FIJI® Water, POM Wonderful®, JUSTIN® Wine, Teleflora®, Wonderful® Seedless Lemons, and Wonderful® Halos® Citrus. To learn more about our programs and read our entire Corporate Social Responsibility report, click here.

This position will be based at our West Los Angeles, CA office. We work a hybrid schedule with an in-office requirement Monday-Wednesday and the option to work remotely on Thursday and Friday.

Job Description

The Lead Healthcare Data Analyst will use clinical, operational, and financial data to measure organizational performance and guide continuous improvement efforts to maximize clinic efficiency and population health improvement. This Healthcare Data Analyst position requires knowledge of EMRs, experience with clinical operations, and data analytics. The ideal candidate would be a sharp analytical thinker who is eager to play a role in transforming healthcare through data; strategy consulting is a plus.

This Lead Healthcare Data Analyst position reports directly to the Senior Manager for Data Analytics alongside frequent engagement with the Chief Medical Officer.
• Conduct regular and ad hoc health data reporting in support of day-to-day, monthly, and annual clinic operations
• Design, build, and maintain reporting tools using data from our Electronic Medical Record (EMR), Epic, to support health-related data-driven decision making at all levels, from front-line staff to executive leadership, as well as to support company-wide Health Benefits planning and tracking
• Support clinic operations by developing standard processes for data-related use of the EMR in daily work
• Train clinical staff on data-related use of the EMR and standard processes, as well as develop processes to audit flow to ensure standard work and data accuracy for both short-term and long-term reporting
• Liaise with Health IT vendors used by the clinic in support of data analytics
• Review quarterly updates released by the EMR system and ensure they are tested, communicated to staff, and optimized for use by clinic staff
• Proactively identify areas for improvement across health and wellness programs and coordinate solutions with staff, implementing necessary measures to gauge efficacy as part of continuous improvement cycles
• Use health care analytics to mine clinical data to measure clinic efficiency and opportunities for improved patient experience, treatment, and cost reduction, including necessary historical data cleanup
• Develop and share presentations to communicate findings to team members at all levels, from the clinic floor to the board room
• Maintain data privacy and confidentiality policies and procedures
• Complete other duties as assigned by clinical and CSR leadership
• Requires travel between our clinics in the Central Valley (Lost Hills & Delano, CA)

Qualifications
• Bachelor's degree required with preferred concentration in data analytics, business, public health, marketing, or statistics
• Master's degree preferred, preferably in health or data related
• Certified health data analyst Certification or equivalent preferred
• 2+ years of experience with data analysis, report design, and project management
• Experience with SQL/database querying and Excel
• Experience with Epic and its related reporting systems, including business objects, Clarity, and Javelin
• Strong project management skills, having managed and successfully completed diverse projects preferred
• Basic financial acumen and experience in population health or clinical data analysis strongly preferred
• Demonstrated passion for improving the healthcare system and helping underserved communities

Additional Information

Wonderful's dedication to you:
• Pay Range: $110,000 - $125,000 and is eligible for a discretionary bonus. Final compensation will be dependent upon skills & experience.
• Competitive benefits packing including Medical, Vision, Dental, 401k, PTO, sick days, paid holidays, and tuition reimbursement program
• Wonderful Giving (www.wonderfulgiving.com) -- allowing you to donate company money to a cause of your choice
• Company focus on health and wellness including WonderfulNow, a robust suite of company wellness offerings focused on supporting our employees
• Access to many Wonderful Company perks including the corporation health clinic and fitness center

In this dynamic position, you are responsible for the collection, analysis and reporting of sales related data in an on-going effort to increase overall sales productivity. If you are passionate about creating standard and custom reports, conduct quantitative and qualitative target analysis, internal support to maintain data integrity within the CRM, we want to talk to you!

YOUR DAY-TO-DAY:
• Compiling, analyzing, and reporting sales data.
• Monitoring, and analyzing competitive activity, customer, and market trends.
• Providing actionable insights to guide the sales and marketing teams
• Review past and current sales data to determine trends in productivity
• Present actionable information and insights
• Create new reports and dashboards
• Support Sales Management: KPI/Scorecard development and distribution, maintain weekly/monthly/annual reporting.

• Support initiatives for data integrity and normalization
• Other duties as assigned

• Excellent oral and written communication skills, ability to interact effectively with all levels of management.
• Excellent project management skills, and effective time management skills.

description:
Job Scope:

This position is located in Southern California and requires in office presence at least once per week, depending upon the project.

The Operations Data Analyst, under the direction of the Compliance and PMO Manager or appointed representative, will gather, analyze and correct operations data for the organization, supporting management and leadership in making informed and objective business and policy decisions.

Primary Duties/Responsibilities:
• Collaborates with operations and business leaders to understand management objectives and data housed in internal application systems.
• Understands business processes and workflows pertinent to entering and populating data sets in the application systems.
• Ensures data integrity by cleaning up and correcting data sets in the systems that were
• entered for testing purposes, and
• analyzes data sets for correctness, accuracy and completeness.
• Establishes, prepares and maintains exception reports from the application systems to be used by users and management.
• Prepares and distributes or delivers reports that identify, explain, and evaluate problems and available solutions.
• Selects computational or data manipulation methods to be used in research and analysis.
• Applies validation and testing models to data.
• Develops mathematical models and/or creates simulation models of problems, applying expected constants and variables, restrictions, alternatives, numerical parameters, and conflicting objectives.
• Performs other duties as assigned.

Required Skills/Abilities:
• Excellent analytical and mathematical skills with the ability to create and conduct simulation models, data reduction and correction, and trend analysis.
• Excellent organizational skills and attention to detail.
• Familiarity with application systems and data sets software (ERP, CRM and the likes)

Education and Experience:
• Bachelor's degree in Mathematics or related field required;
• Prior related experience preferred.
• Degree in computer science and/or statistics preferred and desirable.
• Experience in analyzing large data sets and databases.
• Experience with WellSky and HRIS (ADP) systems would be helpful.

Language Skills:
• Ability to read and understand short instructions, correspondence, and memos
• Ability to effectively communicate through written and verbal language
• Ability to effectively present information in one-on-one, group situations and other employees of the organization in a professional manner

Reasoning Abilities:
• Ability to evaluate situations and make complex decisions using critical thinking and reasoning.

description:
Junior Energy Data Analyst job at Verdani Partners. Carlsbad, CA.

Title : Junior Energy Data Analyst

Position Type : Full-time

Reporting Location : Remote

Schedule : Mon-Fri

Salary Range : $60,000 - $65,000/year

Reports to : Associate Engineering Manager

OVERVIEW

Verdani Partners is seeking a motivated Junior Energy Data Analyst to join our engineering team. The ideal candidate would fill an important role dedicated to one of Verdani’s large commercial real estate portfolio clients enhancing data coverage and quality in collaboration with the ESG team, engineering, and the property teams. This role involves regular quarterly data requests to property teams, close collaboration with key stakeholders and vendors including Measurabl and Redaptive to address data gaps, and make ongoing adjustments to data input sources, all aimed at ensuring the continuous improvement of data coverage and quality. 

This applicant would coordinate directly with our clients; therefore, they must also have superior communication, writing, and presentation skills.

Please see the “About Us” section below or visit our website () to learn more about our firm.

RESPONSIBILITIES

Primary:
• Excellent excel and data management skills
• ENERGY STAR Portfolio Manager experience (Strongly Desired)
• Work with utilities to request aggregated building data through their processes

Secondary:
• Familiarity with building systems and local/state benchmarking regulations
• Proven ability to manage, manipulate and analyze utility billing and usage data (energy, water, waste)

PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE & QUALIFICATIONS

We recognize that the job requirements may vary, and that not every candidate may possess all the required or preferred experience. We will consider candidates who demonstrate a combination of the required and preferred experience, as well as a proactive and positive Can Do attitude in their professional approach.

Required:
• Bachelor's Degree: Engineering, Environmental Engineering, Environmental Science, Engineering Technology, Energy Management, or another related field.
• Excellent written and verbal communication skills

Preferred:
• LEED Green Associate, LEED Accredited Professional – EBOM, Certified Energy Manager, or Certified Energy Auditor

PLATFORMS & SOFTWARE

Required:
• Advanced Proficiency in Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook)

Preferred:
• Experience using ENERGY STAR Portfolio Manager

WORKING CONDITIONS AND PHYSICAL DEMANDS

During the execution of job responsibilities, the employee should expect the following conditions and demands associated with the role:
• Remaining in a stationary position for prolonged periods of time at a desk and working on a computer
• Repetitive motions involving the wrists, hands, and/or fingers
• Occasional light to moderate lifting, bending, stooping, kneeling, or crouching may be necessary
• Close vision requirements due to computer work
• Adequate hearing for effective communication in-person and/or on the telephone
• Ability to move objects weighting up to 25 pounds occasionally, 10 pounds frequently, and/or 5 pounds continuously.
• The job is performed indoors in a traditional office setting where moderate noise levels may be present.

Reasonable accommodations are available upon request to enable individuals to perform the essential functions of the job.

LANGUAGE REQUIREMENTS
• Fluent in English communication, both oral and written.

ADDITIONAL POSITION RELATED DETAILS
• Applicant must be authorized to work in the United States.

ABOUT VERDANI PARTNERS

Verdani Partners is a leading ESG consulting firm dedicated to advancing sustainability in the built environment on a global scale. Our mission-driven organization comprises an international team of experts with over 25 years of experience in real estate, sustainability, and ESG. We specialize in greening new and existing large building portfolios and supporting corporate sustainability needs. Verdani manages ESG programs for over 20 real estate firms with over $660 billion AUM and more than 8,900 properties across 1.3 billion square feet of diversified, global portfolios. Our core services include climate resilience, decarbonization, net zero strategies, healthy buildings, biodiversity, DEI initiatives, data management, green building certifications, ESG frameworks, regulatory and annual reporting, ESG education, and stakeholder engagement. Our clients consistently rank #1, #2, and in the top five among their peers on global real estate ESG benchmarks such as GRESB and A to A+ on PRI.

Verdani’s corporate ESG, technical services, communications, and green building certifications departments, along with our key program verticals and ESG workforce development programs, bring an impressive breadth of expertise to each portfolio and project. Our approach is to identify and prioritize effective solutions that can be sustained over the life of the building, adding economic, social, and environmental value along the way. As a GRESB Global Partner, GRESB Training Partner, and member of the GRESB Benchmarking Committee, we actively participate with USGBC, ULI Greenprint, and Nareit. Since 2023, Verdani has been a Certified B Corporation™, part of a global community of businesses that meet high standards of social and environmental impact, pledging to use business as a force for good®. Our talented team of experts combines passion with an above-and-beyond commitment to sustainability, delivering exceptional results for our clients while maintaining a balance between work and family needs.

Verdani is a fast-growing organization that prioritizes community and employee well-being. We offer an array of excellent benefits, including flexible work schedules, health insurance contributions, life and short-term disability insurance, paid time off, a 401k program with employer contributions, an employee assistance program, annual educational and conference allowances, and monthly internet and food stipends.

Joining the Verdani team means becoming part of something bigger. We are a diverse and dedicated group that feels more like a family, united by a shared goal: making a difference in the world now and for future generations. Our environment is laid-back yet professional, filled with talented individuals who believe in making work enjoyable and impactful.

Verdani is an equal opportunity employer. We welcome all applicants regardless of race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, veteran, or disability status. Verdani is committed to providing a work environment free of discrimination and harassment, ensuring equal employment opportunities for all employees.

WELLNESS & BENEFITS

Verdani is supportive of employee satisfaction, growth, health, and wellbeing. We offer many benefits including:
• Medical, dental, vision, life, and short-term disability insurance
• Paid vacation, holidays, sick leave, and volunteer time
• Paid parental leave
• Extra vacation days based on tenure
• Floating holidays
• Employee Assistance Program (EAP)
• Referral Program
• Bereavement Leave
• Annual allowance for professional certifications, training, memberships and attending professional conferences
• Monthly internet/food stipend
• Annual equipment allowance
• Annual support allowance
• Flexible work arrangements including work from home, flexible working hours, and flexible schedules with supervisor approval
• 401K program with employer contributions
• and more!

Thank you for your interest in this position at Verdani Partners!
• *As a result of the large number of applications we receive, we are unable to provide immediate individual updates on your application status. However, if you are chosen for an interview, you will receive direct communication via email.

Beware of imposters posing as recruiters! Always verify that emails, including those regarding job interviews and offers, come from Verdani's official email addresses, such as @applytojob.com or @verdani.com. Please note that we never send checks or request payment for equipment.

description:
ABOUT THE BRAND:

Callaway Golf is the leading manufacturer of premium golf clubs, balls, performance gear and accessories worldwide. Through an unwavering commitment to innovation, we push the limits of performance and create demonstrably superior products designed to make every golfer a better golfer.

Our company is a blend of experience and diverse backgrounds, and together we look to move the game forward, and we want top-notch people to join us in that mission!

By joining Callaway Golf, you also join part of the portfolio of brands within Topgolf Callaway Brands, an unrivaled tech-enabled Modern Golf and active lifestyle company delivering leading golf equipment, apparel, and entertainment, with a portfolio of global brands including Topgolf, Callaway Golf, TravisMathew, Toptracer, Odyssey, OGIO, Jack Wolfskin, and World Golf Tour (“WGT”). “Modern Golf” is the dynamic and inclusive ecosystem that includes both on-course and off-course golf. For more information, please visit https://www.topgolfcallawaybrands.com

Job Overview

The Principal Data & Visualization Analyst will analyze consumer data, generate business insights, and develop reporting to identify and recommend growth opportunities for Topgolf Callaway Brands. This position requires fluency in data and data modeling languages (SQL, Python) along with the business acumen required to drive customer KPIs. In this role, the analyst will collaborate with marketing teams across multiple brands and a centralized data engineering team. The ideal candidate is comfortable collaborating and communicating across various roles and levels, including leadership.

Roles And Responsibilities
• Query and analyze data within Snowflake to track marketing KPIs and assess business health.
• Effectively present insights and educate both internal and external leadership teams.
• Interpret data and dashboards from the perspective of diverse internal stakeholders.
• Design and develop impactful reporting and visualizations
• Partner with internal business teams and brands to brainstorm design ideas, layouts, and functionality throughout the development process.
• Work directly with vendors to resolve issues and collaborate on product improvements.
• Run basic ML experiments like classification, clustering, and regression for business insights and decisions.
• Use Power BI's integration with Python to conduct ML experimentation within the reports.
• Collaborate with cross-functional teams to ensure timely project completion.

TECHNICAL COMPETENCIES
• Advanced skills in SQL, specifically for Snowflake, to write efficient queries for marketing data analysis.
• Ideally has experience coding in Python for ML and data pipeline work
• Expertise in DAX for creating advanced calculations, KPIs, and complex logic.
• Experience in embedding Python scripts in Power BI for more advanced data analysis and custom visualizations.
• Understanding of marketing KPIs (Customer Lifetime Value, Customer Acquisition Cost, ROI, etc.) and how to structure data models and dashboards to reflect these metrics.
• Proven ability to enhance efficiency through automation.

Education And Experience
• Bachelor’s degree in computer science, business administration, or other “STEM” programs
• Eight or more years of experience in consumer data analysis and reporting,
• Six or more years of experience working with BI tools such as Microsoft Power BI
• Four years of experience working with large databases and data sets.
• Knowledge of golf and sports industry is a plus.

Inclusion & Diversity: As a purpose-led, performance driven company, we strive to foster a culture of belonging based on respect, connection, openness and authenticity. We are committed to building and maintaining a workplace that celebrates the diversity of our associates, supporting them to bring their authentic selves to work every day.

DE&I and EEOC:

Inclusion & Diversity: As a purpose-led, performance driven company, we strive to foster a culture of belonging based on respect, connection, openness and authenticity. We are committed to building and maintaining a workplace that celebrates the diversity of our associates, supporting them to bring their authentic selves to work every day.

If your experience is close to what we’re looking for, please consider applying. Experience comes in many forms, skills are transferable, and passion goes a long way. We know that diverse backgrounds and experiences make for the best problem-solving and creative thinking, which is why we’re dedicated to adding new perspectives to the team and encourage everyone to apply. We look forward to learning more about you.

ARE YOU READY TO MAKE THE TURN? APPLY TODAY!

description:
The pay range above represents the minimum and maximum rate for this position in California. Factors that may be used to determine where newly hired employees will be placed in the pay range include the employee specific skills and qualifications, relevant years of experience and comparison to other employees already in this role. Most often, a newly hired employee will be placed below the midpoint of the range. Salary range will vary for remote positions outside of California and future increases will be based on the pay band for the city and state you reside in.

Work Culture:

GCHP strives to create an inclusive, highly collaborative work culture where our people are empowered to grow and thrive. This philosophy enables us to create the health plan of the future and do our best work – Together.

GCHP promotes a flexible work environment. Employees may work from a home location or in the GCHP office for all or part of their regular workweek (see disclaimer).

GCHP’s focuses on 5 Core Values in the workplace:

• Integrity

• Accountability

• Collaboration

• Trust

• Respect

Disclaimers:

• Flexible work schedule is based on job duties, department, organization, or business need.

• Gold Coast Health Plan will not sponsor applicants for work visas.

POSITION SUMMARY

Senior Data Analyst/EDI is responsible for managing and analyzing electronic data interchange (EDI) transactions, ensuring accurate data flow between the organization and external partners, including providers, payers, and vendors. This role involves troubleshooting, maintaining compliance with healthcare industry standards, and leveraging data insights to support decision-making and operational efficiency.

Reasonable Accommodations Statement

To accomplish this job successfully, an individual must be able to perform, with or without reasonable accommodation, each essential function satisfactorily. Reasonable accommodations may be made to help enable qualified individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.

Amount of Travel Required: 5-10%

ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS

Job Function & Responsibilities

The following duties are expected to be performed for both the Medicare, Medicaid and any new business units:

• Performs regular system monitoring to verify the integrity, health and availability of all systems and key processes, reviewing application and system logs and ensuring completion of scheduled jobs

• Responsible for ensuring that data received from external and internal parties (such as our Clients and Vendor partners) are successfully ingested and available for processing in our transactional systems, while also ensuring that file extracts for external and internal business partners are produced and delivered on the agreed upon schedule.

• Assists in the development and optimization of file exchange process monitoring tools and processes

• Ownership over the version of all EDI mapping documentation

• Participates in Data Governance Council meetings

• Oversee the integration of various data sources and ensure seamless data flow across different systems within the organization

• Partner with Data Engineering and Data Governance on the accuracy of the data models and the outputs to optimize operational performance and achieve financial targets

• Provide ad-hoc analysis to support L2 inquiry requests

• Assist in managing EDI projects, system upgrades, implementations, and enhancements, ensuring successful completion within agreed timelines and budgets

• Partners with Vendors on issue resolution

MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS

Education & Experience:

• BA/BS in MIS, statistics, computer science, mathematics, information management, business, or a related field Preferred

• 4+ years of experience of performing data analysis and reporting development

• 4+ years of experience with writing SQL queries and stored procedures with relational databases

• Experienced with supporting healthcare business transactions for Medicare and Medicaid business

• IT Service desk experience

• Comfortable working with large raw data files (Csv, Txt , EDI) is necessary (editing, manipulating, searching.

• Intermediate level of proficiency in MS packages including ADO

• Ability to plan, implement, test, and troubleshoot complex technology, software, and system solutions

• Understanding of statistical tools

• Passion for problem-solving and customer service

• Experience with Health Insurance or Health Care related data X12 EDI, FHIR, and other structured JSON, XML, or proprietary formats

• Strong ability to translate insights from the data

Equivalent In lieu of degree:

Will accept experience in any combination of academic education, professional training, or work experience, which demonstrates the ability to perform the duties of the position.

4 -5 years of EDI experience must be added in lieu of a bachelor’s degree.

KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS & ABILITIES

Preferred Qualifications:

Additional experience or related experience in managed care, Medi-Cal, Medicare, leadership experience, etc. • Proven experience working as an EDI Analyst or in a similar role.

• Experienced with WEDI SNP Editing

• Proficient experience with FHIR formats and tooling

• Strong knowledge of EDI protocols and standards, such as ANSI X12, EDIFACS, XML, and AS2.

• Proficient in EDI mapping and translation tools, such as Gentran, Sterling Integrator, or similar software.

• Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to identify and troubleshoot issues related to data communication and system integration.

• Solid understanding of business processes and workflows in the healthcare industry

• Strong attention to detail and accuracy, with the ability to handle large volumes of data and ensure data integrity

• Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to work effectively with cross-functional teams and external partners.

• In-depth knowledge of EDI protocols, standards, and best practices

• Experience in working with EDI VANs (Value-Added Networks)

• Knowledge of industry-specific EDI documents and transactions, such as 837, 835, 834, 820, 274, 837 encounters, and 27x series and their corresponding responses

• Tableau, Power BI

• Excellent Problem-solving skills

Technology & Software Skills: Advanced computer skills in MS Office products.

Certifications & Licenses: A valid and current Driver's License, Auto Insurance, and professional licensures required

Competency Statements

• Management Skills - Ability to organize and direct oneself and effectively supervise others.

• Business Acumen - Ability to grasp and understand business concepts and issues.

• Decision Making - Ability to make critical decisions while following company procedures.

• Goal Oriented - Ability to focus on a goal and obtain a pre-determined result.

• Interpersonal - Ability to get along well with a variety of personalities and individuals.

• Diversity Oriented - Ability to work effectively with people regardless of their age, gender, race, ethnicity, religion, or job type.

• Time Management - Ability to utilize the available time to organize and complete work within given deadlines.

• Consensus Building - Ability to bring about group solidarity to achieve a goal.

• Relationship Building - Ability to effectively build relationships with customers and co-workers.

• Presentation Skills - Ability to effectively present information publicly.

• Delegating Responsibility - Ability to allocate authority and/or task responsibility to appropriate people.

• Leadership - Ability to influence others to perform their jobs effectively and to be responsible for making decisions.

• Strategic Planning - Ability to develop a vision for the future and create a culture in which the long-range goals can be achieved.

• Ethical - Ability to demonstrate conduct conforming to a set of values and accepted standards.

• Judgment - The ability to formulate a sound decision using the available information.

• Communication, Oral - Ability to communicate effectively with others using the spoken word.

• Communication, Written - Ability to communicate in writing clearly and concisely.

• Problem Solving - Ability to find a solution for or to deal proactively with work-related problems.

description:
Responsibilities
• Data Quality Assurance:
• * Perform routine data audits, validations and reconciliations to ensure accuracy and completeness.
• * Identify data inconsistencies, errors or gaps and work with relevant teams to resolve them.
• Develop and implement data quality control standards, policies and procedures.
• Discover, analyze, and scope data requests from internal business users.
• Process Improvement:
• * Create high-level process models (system interface diagrams, workflow & swim lane diagrams, data flow diagrams) to represent processes for the area under analysis.
• Empower the business by creating value through the increased adoption of data standards, industry best practices and business intelligence.
• Analyze data workflows and recommend improvements to optimize efficiency and accuracy.
• Support the development of dashboards and reports to monitor data quality metrics.
• Stakeholder Support:
• * Serve as the primary liaison for the State of Nevada’s internal stakeholders focused on statewide data, providing expert level support for data related inquiries and issues.
• Partner with the State Highway Office, DPS Office of Traffic Safety (OTS) and Nevada Department of Public Safety (NDOT) to understand the data requirements and goals for State and local agencies.
• Partner with Traffic Records and the Fatality Analysis Reporting System (FARS) to ensure OTS is providing accurate, current and beneficial, traffic records data that will benefit stakeholders and policy makers.
• Translate complex data findings into actionable insights for stakeholders.
• Offer training and guidance on data governance, quality and best practices.
• Documentation and Reporting:
• * Maintain comprehensive documentation of data quality processes, issues and resolutions.
• Prepare and present regular reports on data quality status and improvements to stakeholders

Qualifications
• Bachelor's or master's degree in information technology, computer science, business administration, economics, or related field.
• 4 or more years of experience with data analysis & data profiling in project, business requirements definition.
• Strong understanding of data governance principles and practices
• Proficiency in data analysis tools (eg SQL, Excel, Power Bi, Tableau)
• Proficiency in collaborative tools (eg Sharepoint, TEAMS)
• Experience working with large datasets and data management systems.
• Familiarity with state government operations or public sector data
• Strong communication and interpersonal skills to effectively collaborate with diverse stakeholders.
• Analytical mindset with problem solving skills.
• Attention to detail and commitment to data accuracy.
• Ability to work independently and manage multiple priorities.
• Strong collaboration and stakeholder engagement skills.
• Must be located anywhere in the state of Nevada or College Station, TX
title: Data Quality Support Analyst

description:
Who are Taco Bell?
Taco Bell is a leading Mexican-inspired quick service restaurant brand that is a part of Yum! Brands, Inc. which includes Pizza Hut and KFC. Founded on innovation and passion with Glen Bell bringing tacos to the masses in a world of hot dog and hamburger stands in 1962, today we have nearly 7,000 restaurants in the United States and over 400 restaurants in 27 countries outside of the United States. The future holds 2,000 more restaurants across the globe within the next decade. It’s easy to see we’re in the business of making tacos, but at heart, we’re a business that’s fueled by the Live Más energy and passion of people serving people

What is “Live Más”?
Equally important to the job role and responsibilities is making sure the Supply Chain Data Analyst can represent the amazing Live Más! culture that is Taco Bell. At Taco Bell, we embrace breakthrough thinking and innovative ideas that continue to differentiate us from our competitors. We have a maniacal focus on our customers, never follow, and always celebrate the accomplishments of our people. If you want to have fun serving great food to our customers, we would love to meet with you.

About the Job:
The Supply Chain Data Analyst will be part of UK & Europe Supply Chain Team, a dynamic team that values collaboration, resourcefulness, and enthusiasm. You will closely work with the pan-EU supply chain team, internal and external partners helping to leverage data and insights to report, continuously optimise performance and deliver our supply chain ambitions. You will support the Taco Bell Europe supply chain team by providing actionable insights and analytics to drive decision-making, enhance operational efficiency, and improve supplier performance. The role is instrumental in ensuring accurate forecasting, cost management, and supply chain optimisation across multiple European markets.

This position is based out of UK office and is ideal for individuals with high accountability, strong analytical skills, great attention to detail, intellectual curiosity, and a drive for results. In this role you will:

Automate the short, medium, and long terms demand baseline forecast at SKU item level in Power BI
Collect, clean, and analyse data from multiple sources including supplier reports, sales forecasts and market trends
Develop and maintain dashboards to track KPIs such as cost of sales, supplier performance, forecast vs actuals, stock holding & weeks cover
Develop and provide weekly reporting to the Supply Chain leadership team
Creation of full end to end commercial reporting – full visibility of stock in the network
Review historical trends, research demand drivers, prepare forecast data, develop statistical models, and evaluate forecast results
Perform root cause analysis on key forecast deviations. Supports Business, Marketing, Logistics, and production strategies and identify opportunities to meet market needs
In collaboration with Logistics and Buying Team, ensure the right stock is in the right place at the right time to deliver customer requirements at DC level
Work with Marketing and Finance teams to combine, refine and publish total business demand plan (in applicable levels / aggregated views e.g., by product, by category etc.)
Create insights from business forecast analysis to drive continuous improvement (specifically from a proactiveness point of view) in Supply Chain
Incorporate market intelligence into demand plans
Lead promotional activity forecast planning at SKU item level
Support cost modelling for new market entries
Work with Procurement team to develop, enhance and simplify processes

Is this you?

Minimum of 2-4 years experience in supply chain analytics, procurement, or logistics management
Data and analysis-driven with advanced Excel skills
Advanced proficiency with data visualisation tools (e.g. Power BI)
Self-starter capable of solving complex problems with limited data
Bachelor’s degree preferred
Experience working at International restaurant business, food retailer, food supplier, or in food manufacturing is a plus
Demonstrated ability to plan and coordinate workflow and outputs efficiently across multiple functional groups
Strong communications (presentation, verbal, writing) and relationship development skills
Strong process creation and optimization
Entrepreneurial
Commercial thinker
High level of intellectual curiosity
Ability to influence diverse customers in cross-functional setting

Why Taco Bell?
We truly believe that where you work matters, and we know a thing or two about what makes employees happy. Join us on our mission of feeding people’s lives with Más!

We are about more than just building restaurants—we connect with our fans through their passions including sports, gaming, and music
We know that employees want a company they can live and grow with; they crave a unique culture that fosters creativity and encourages pursuit of passion, and they look for opportunities to take risks, develop skills and learn in ways that fit their lifestyle
We foster a culture of authenticity and believe all people can make a difference

Work-Hard, Play-Hard:

Company and performance-related bonus
Generous pension with up to 11% company contribution
Private healthcare with the option to increase to include family cover
Annual holiday allowance starts at 25 days with the option to buy or sell up to 5 extra days per year. After 5 years’ service, annual holiday allowance increases to 30 days
Competitive parental leave and flexible return to work options
Wellbeing Reimbursement – A fund to claim back costs throughout the year that support your well-being such as vitamins subscriptions, language lessons, gym membership
Flexible and Voluntary benefits including Dental Insurance, Health Screening and Gym Discounts

At Taco Bell, we Live Más and invite you to do the same. Take a seat at our table. Bring your voice. Bring you, just as you are, a Cultural Rebel. We want you to be your best self!

Taco Bell is proud to be an equal opportunity employer and is committed to equity, inclusion, and belonging for all dimensions of diversity.
title: Supply Chain Data Analyst

description:
The Strategic Research and Analytics team helps shape how we use data to inform strategies and investments across Marketing, Communications, and Corporate Responsibility functions (M&C) at Intuit. We are looking to expand our capabilities in data analytics, data science and data engineering. This role will actively partner with analysts, engineers, data scientists, researchers, marketers, communicators, and product managers across a variety of initiatives to deliver operational dashboards that drive business decisions and perform analyses that uncover new insights. If you are an individual with strong analytical skills and a passion for delivering data-driven insights, then this job is for you.
Responsibilities
• Create and manage success metrics and leading indicators that provide a holistic understanding of performance of key M&C initiatives
• Develop and maintain data pipelines, data collection processes, and dashboards for operational reporting and exploratory analysis, and provide training to empower stakeholders to self-serve for Intuit brand health and reputation KPIs, internal/external communications, and Intuit for Education
• Prepare and present reports and dashboards that measure performance for internal employees and external communications (social media, earned media)
• Measure the impact of marketing activities using advanced analytical approaches (e.g., attribution, a/b tests, geo experiments, and incrementality models) to help inform strategies, plans, and tactics on an on-going basis
• Establish and promote best practices for reporting strategies, data visualization, data interpretation and data integrity
• Communicate and influence across all levels of the organization. Present analytical findings and recommendations in a clear and concise way to non-technical audiences, both in oral and written presentations
• Identify opportunities for developing new data sources, and provide technical leadership around making those data sources high-quality and broadly available
• Pursue data quality, troubleshoot data anomalies, validate data accuracy, and drive issues to resolution
• Collaborate with technical and business stakeholders across different teams and businesses on cross-functional projects or analytics capabilities
title: Senior Marketing Data Analyst

description:
Western Alliance Bank is hiring a Data Analyst, Business Reporting with 3 - 5 years of experience. Based in United States - Westlake Village, CA and with Hybrid ways of working.

Job description and responsibilities:

Under the direction of the VP, Business Analytics Manager, the Business Reporting and Data Analyst will work closely with department staff, technical team members, project managers, business users, and IT staff to deliver from minor enhancements to complex projects. The individual will be researching and analyzing information, anticipating and recognizing problems and opportunities, creatively developing possible solutions, evaluating alternatives and, using sound judgment, determine the best course of action. The ideal candidate will be a driven individual who is logical, analytical and detailed oriented, has some mortgage experience, and has a good understanding of database administration. This position will be part of the CL Business Analytics team, which develops reporting and routines to ensure consistent communication between Correspondent Lending and related corporate counterparties.

Responsibilities

What we are looking for:
• Compile analytical and statistical reports as needed
• Formulate, define and recommend scope and format of reports
• Oversee provision of ad hoc management reports
• Review information for accuracy and reconciles data on a regular basis
• Provide internal and external data needs
• Define, review and implement best practices for data entry, software security, reporting and information management within database
• Map and load data into development environments
• Elicit business and functional requirements and document them in JIRA / Confluence / Atlassian

Reporting to the Supervising Staff Analyst, Health under the direction of the Director, this position offers an exciting opportunity to lead innovative projects transforming specialty care delivery in Los Angeles County and to engage with high level executives and clinical leaders across LA Health Services within health administration, clinical care, operations and data analytics/informatics.

Duties will include but are not limited to:
• Provide project management of certain initiatives and priorities of the specialty care team, in collaboration with the Director, facility specialty leaders, service line chiefs and other clinical or administrative staff.
• Engage and collaborate with key system leaders, front line staff, managers, workgroups and data team around performance improvement (PI) goals.
• Oversee management of specialty workgroups and system committees working towards key specialty care deliverables.
• Support workgroups in the development, management, and optimization of clinical guidelines (Expected Practices).
• Participate in maintenance, review and optimization of clinical guidelines to ensure they are organized, accurate, and current.
• Support efforts to measure adherence and optimize the integration of Expected Practices into the clinical workflow.
• Perform data management and analysis to support specialty care-focused data needs including the development of targeted reports, data dashboards and scorecards.
• Support other specialty care projects and programs as needed.
Desirable Qualifications:
• Proficient with Microsoft Office Suite (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Teams, etc.)
• High degree of emotional intelligence with track record of collaboration and commitment to fostering Just Culture
• Excellent communication skills and ability to work in a flexible, collaborative, team-oriented environment
• Strong personal accountability and attention to detail
• Experience working with providers, nurses, and other clinical team members
• Familiarity with DHS clinical, information and data systems, including ORCHID, ELM, CEDAR, SharePoint, eConsult, etc.
The position is open to all permanent County of Los Angeles employees who have successfully completed their initial probationary period and currently hold the payroll title of Staff Analyst, Health.

-OR-

Reachable on the DHS Staff Analyst, Health certification list. APPLICATIONS MUST BE FILED ONLINE ONLY.

Candidates interested in this transfer opportunity must attach the following to their online application:

1. Cover Letter
2. Resume
3. Copies of last two (2) performance evaluations
4. Three (3) Professional References

All submitted documents will be evaluated. Only the most qualified candidates will be contacted by the hiring manager for an interview. Employment is contingent upon passing a background check and review of personnel records.

If you are unable to attach the required documents online, you may email your information to:

description:
At InStride, people are our purpose.

We believe that investing in people is the most powerful way to drive success—for individuals and organizations alike.

As a public benefit corporation, we partner with leading employers to unlock opportunities for their employees, providing access to top-tier education programs that align with their employees’ career goals and the company’s business goals.

Our mission goes beyond skill-building; we're here to empower our partners’ employees to advance their careers, elevate their expertise, and achieve meaningful personal and professional growth.

No matter the team you’re on, our dedication to the success of our partners and their employees is what drives us. If you're passionate about making a difference and driving educational and professional advancement, InStride is the place for you.

To get a better feel for our culture

What we're looking for:

InStride is seeking an experienced Sr. Data Analyst to join our growing Data Analytics team. As a Sr. Data Analyst reporting to the Director of Data Analytics, you will play a crucial role in transforming data into actionable insights and recommendations that drive strategic decisions across the business. You’ll collaborate closely with stakeholders across the company, providing them with data-driven insights to support growth and operational efficiency. Your work will contribute to building a strong data culture, enabling key business partners to self-serve data through dynamic dashboards and make informed decisions using company-wide metrics.

Skills we’d love to see you show off:
• Data Analysis & Reporting: Analyze complex datasets from Databricks to provide actionable insights across internal teams such as sales, marketing, finance, and product. Build and maintain dynamic Tableau dashboards that empower stakeholders to self-serve and track key metrics.
• Stakeholder Collaboration: Work closely with business partners to understand needs and provide data-driven insights for strategic decisions. Serve as a trusted advisor to business stakeholders, helping them interpret data and apply it effectively.
• Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) and Metrics: Identify, define, and track company-wide key performance indicators (KPIs) aligned with business goals. Continuously monitor and evaluate the effectiveness of KPIs, suggesting new metrics to support organizational consistency.
• Data Validation & Integrity: Ensure accuracy and consistency in data reporting, collaborating with analytics engineers to maintain data quality. Validate data models, ensuring alignment with business requirements and optimization for reporting.
• Data Visualization & Presentation: Create clear and compelling visualizations to communicate complex data to both technical and non-technical stakeholders. Present insights and recommendations in a concise, actionable format to business leaders and teams.
• Documentation & Best Practices: Maintain thorough documentation of data models, analysis processes, dashboards, and business rules. Ensure stakeholders understand key metrics and methodologies through clear and accessible documentation.

Who you are:
• 5+ years of experience in a data analysis or business intelligence role.
• Strong expertise in SQL and visualization tools such as Tableau or Power BI.
• Excellent business acumen with the ability to quickly understand complex business processes and relationships between data.
• Proficient in statistics and comfortable applying statistical methods to analyze data.
• Experience identifying, defining, and tracking KPIs that support strategic business initiatives.
• Exceptional communication and presentation skills, with a knack for making data insights easy to understand for non-technical stakeholders.
• Experience working in a collaborative environment with technical teams and non-technical stakeholders.
• Experience in the edtech or education sector is a plus.

How you will create impact:
• Enable key business partners to make data-driven decisions by providing timely and insightful analysis.
• Collaborate with engineers to ensure the reporting infrastructure supports efficient and accurate business insights.
• Identify and track key performance indicators (KPIs) that drive business success and continuously evaluate their effectiveness.
• Improve data visualization and storytelling capabilities across the organization, increasing trust in and reliance on data.
• Help drive business performance by uncovering trends and opportunities.

Target base compensation amount for this role outlined below. Final offer amounts are determined by multiple factors including candidate experience and expertise and may vary from the amounts shown below.

$95,000 - $110,000 USD

We are looking for someone who is not only technically skilled, but also enthusiastic about making a meaningful impact. If this description resonates with you, we're excited about the possibility of having you on our team. As a skills-driven employer, we encourage you to apply if there is a skill-fit, even in the absence of years of experience.

Don’t meet every single requirement? Studies have shown that women and people of color are less likely to apply to jobs unless they meet every single qualification. At InStride we are dedicated to building a diverse, inclusive, and authentic workplace, so if you’re excited about this role, but your past experience doesn’t align perfectly with every qualification in the job description, we encourage you to apply anyways. You may be just the right candidate for this role!

Benefits @ InStride

As an organization that champions investing in people, it’s critical we walk the talk. That’s why InStride employees are eligible to enroll in 2,800+ online certificate and degree programs through our Step Forward program. Unlike traditional tuition reimbursement programs, InStride covers your tuition upfront, regardless of your course of study, degree type, or school - eligible to employees starting Day 1.

This role is also eligible for the following benefits:
• 401(k) plan with company match
• Flexible vacation policy
• Paid family leave
• Best-in-class health care benefits
• And more!

InStride Diversity and Inclusion Statement

At InStride, we foster a culture of belonging, we support authenticity and intersectionality, and we embrace and appreciate our differences. We do this by building a diverse pipeline of talent and ensuring equitable access to opportunities, information and leadership. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees.

If you have a disability or special need that requires accommodation, please let your recruiter know.

Policies & Disclosure

InStride recommends employees have their COVID vaccinations. InStride may require employees to have COVID vaccination before entering the office or attending any InStride-related even in the future. However, we do not require this at this time.

For questions on how we use personal information of job applicants, please refer to InStride's Job Applicant Privacy Policy.

Beware of recruiting scams. InStride does not require a financial transaction or any financial account information to be eligible for employment. If you receive a message purporting to be from InStride asking you for a financial transaction, your financial account information, or any other sensitive information, please do not respond and let us know immediately at recruiting@instride.com.

About InStride

InStride is a tech-enabled services company that is pioneering new approaches to workforce education solutions with a mission of driving meaningful social and business outcomes by unlocking access to life-changing education. In collaboration with quality academic institutions, we enable employers to provide career-aligned, debt-free education through a personalized, digital platform and a consultative service model. To learn more, visit: https://www.instride.com/

About the position

As an Advanced Data Analyst for Commercial Excellence at Honeywell Aerospace Technologies, you will play a critical role in driving data-driven decision-making and providing valuable insights to support business growth and operational excellence. This position involves managing analytics projects, collaborating with cross-functional teams, and delivering actionable insights that drive business outcomes in the aerospace industry. You will utilize statistical techniques, machine learning algorithms, and predictive modeling to identify trends, patterns, and opportunities for process improvement and optimization. Your work will directly impact the aerospace industry by providing strategic recommendations based on data insights, which will be crucial for business leaders in understanding their analytical needs. In this role, you will also manage relationships with external vendors and partners to leverage their expertise and capabilities in analytics. You will be responsible for ensuring data integrity, accuracy, and security throughout the analytics process. description:
please send your resume and the job name to:

Permanent position

Brea, CA

Summary:

The Healthcare Analyst provides clinical and financial analysis and reporting for existing clients and provides support for pricing new business.

Essential Duties and Responsibilities:
• Acts with honor and integrity, serving as a role model for the company.
• Analyzes prospective and current client utilization data to identify utilization trends, calculate cost of healthcare and identify opportunities to add value to customers.
• Works with internal business customers to define report and dashboard requirements for use in managing day to day operations more efficiently.
• Assists with the QC/Validation of the data currently being developed into the data warehouse.
• Validates the completeness of potential client data files using various techniques.
• Extracts and compiles both internal and external data elements used in all aspects of the business from client pricing, medical cost management, operational reporting and general financial analysis as required.
• Populates existing pricing model with potential client information and makes suggestions on potential improvements to the model or corresponding presentation/reporting.
• Participates in or conducts presentations to prospective clients regarding pricing methodologies.
• Reconciles capitation payments to eligibility data to ensure monthly payments received are accurate.
• Calculates and analyzes monthly capitation payments made to network providers; identifies and investigates unusual fluctuations and determines root cause of potential problems.
• Conducts recurring and ad hoc provider utilization analyses; prepares meaningful, professional reports for health plans.
• Respects and maintains HIPAA confidentiality guidelines.
• Acts as an interdepartmental liaison between offices, departments, and committees.
• Performs other duties as assigned.

Project Management and Execution:
• Coordinate with other departments across the AO such as IM governance & EDW and support conceptualization and development of reporting/analytical methodologies, solutions and initiatives
• Aid in the development of project plans and strategies as well as execute assigned project plans to deliver solutions in a timely manner
• Support collaboration on roadmaps, dependencies, and execution plans across analytical units and with applicable teams in the organization
• Manage the intake requests across the business units; track and monitor the work to ensure critical milestones are met, identify and report/escalate risks to management appropriately; manage stakeholder relations
• Obtain data, direct/execute reporting/analysis, perform interpretations and conclusions, and prepare recommendations.
• Assist in determining business needs by effectively conducting fact-finding interviews and leveraging various tools and analytical methods and then summarize findings in a coherent manner to develop and propose appropriate solution
• Conduct research studies that include collecting data from various sources, analyzing, trending and presenting the findings and recommendations to management
• Support translation of business requirements and unstructured business issues into data analytic problems
• Perform overall program evaluations (i.e., planning-implementation-completion/analysis-reporting) and other assessments such as change management assessments, workflow optimization assessments, etc.

QUALIFICATION REQUIREMENTS:

EDUCATION and/or EXPERIENCE:

At least a Bachelor's degree with emphasis in Economics, Computer Science, Statistics, Math or Business, or equivalent work experience.
• Minimum of 4-6 years’ work experience in an analytical role
• Master degree in a quantitative field preferred.
• Work experience with line item healthcare claims and PBM information is preferred. OTHER SKILLS and ABILITIES:
• An understanding of CPT, ICD-9, Revenue and DRG codes is preferred.
• Must have expensive experience and proficiency leveraging SQL, including loading data, writing update and select statements, and joining tables.
• Experience with Excel spreadsheets and other office productivity applications to share and present analytic results.
• Experience with SAS.
• Experience with statistical analysis tools such as SAS Office Analytics desired.
• Experience with business Intelligence tools such as SAS Visual Analytics desired.
• Ability to understand and work with a variety of data formats to create charts, graphs, tables, and other visual means of representing key aspects of the data.
• Strong written and verbal communications, including the ability to summarize the results of data analysis for technical and non-technical audiences. Must also be comfortable presenting this information via in person meetings as well as webinar technologies.
• Experience with technical writing preferred.
• Must have strong analytical skills with the ability to develop advanced analytic models (e.g. forecasting).
• Must be skilled at prioritizing assignments and working to ensure all mission critical timeframes and deadlines are met.
• Must be able to work independently and demonstrate initiative and problem solving skills working within a fast paced start up environment

CA EMPLOYEE PRIVACY RIGHTS: https://www.mgae.com/ca-employee-privacy-rights

MGA Entertainment is one of the largest and fastest growing privately held toy and entertainment companies in the world. Headquartered in Los Angeles, and with offices globally, the company creates innovative, proprietary, and licensed consumer products and entertainment properties, including toys, games, dolls, apparel, consumer electronics, home décor, stationery, sporting goods, movies, and television series. The MGA family includes award-winning brands such as L.O.L. Surprise!™, Little Tikes®, Rainbow High™, Shadow High™, Bratz®, MGA’s Miniverse™, Fluffie Stuffiez™ , Na! Na! Na! Surprise™, Micro Games of America™, Baby born® Surprise and Zapf Creation®. For more information, please visit us at www.mgae.com or check us out at LinkedIn, Twitter, Instagram and Facebook.

Job Summary: MGA Entertainment is in search of a Data Analyst with a passion for numbers and a love for toys to help drive the success of our paid media campaigns. As a Data Analyst for the MGA Media team, you will play a key role in analyzing the performance of paid media efforts (such as digital advertising, social media, retail media, influencers, programmatic & display ads, etc.) to provide actionable insights that will improve ROI and consumer engagement. You will work closely with Brand marketing, Creative Services, and Synergy teams to measure the effectiveness of campaigns, identify trends, and recommend strategies for optimization.

Key Responsibilities:
• Data Analysis & Reporting:

Analyze and interpret key metrics from paid media campaigns across multiple platforms (Google Ads, Facebook Ads, Instagram, TikTok, etc.).

Develop and maintain regular reports on campaign performance, highlighting trends, ROI, conversion rates, customer acquisition costs (CAC), and other key performance indicators (KPIs).

Create customized dashboards and visualizations that clearly communicate campaign results and insights to stakeholders.
• Campaign Performance Monitoring:

Track and evaluate the success of campaigns in real-time, providing insights and recommendations to optimize budget allocation and creative strategies.

Assist Media Buyers with A/B testing to determine the most effective messaging, targeting, and bidding strategies for different ad units and platforms.
• Trend Identification & Market Insights:

Monitor industry trends, consumer behavior, and competitive landscape to provide strategic insights on paid media performance and consumer preferences.

Collaborate with marketing and creative teams to suggest new approaches for improving campaign performance.
• Collaboration & Cross-Functional Support:

Partner with media planner/buyers, brand marketing teams, and franchise teams to align campaign objectives and ensure accurate data tracking and reporting.

Assist with the development of data-driven strategies that improve overall media efficiency and drive customer purchase intent and/or conversions.
• Continuous Improvement:

Continuously improve analytics processes, tools, and reporting methods.

Stay current with new media platforms, tools, and analytical techniques that could enhance campaign tracking and performance evaluation.

Qualifications:
• Bachelor’s degree in Data Science, Statistics, Business Analytics, Economics, or a related field.
• Proven experience (5+ years) in data analysis, preferably in digital marketing on the brand or agency side. Experience in the toy industry is a plus.
• Strong proficiency in analytics and data visualization tools such as Google Analytics, Tableau, Power BI, or similar.
• Advanced knowledge of Excel or Google Sheets, with experience in data manipulation and pivot tables.
• Familiarity with digital advertising platforms (theTradeDesk, Google/YouTube Ads, Meta for Business, TikTok Ads Manager, etc.) and the ability to interpret campaign data from these platforms.
• Solid understanding of key performance metrics (i.e. ROAS, VTR, CPV, CTR, CPA), attribution, and conversion tracking.
• Strong attention to detail, critical thinking, and problem-solving skills.
• Excellent communication skills with the ability to present data insights to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.
• Team player with the ability to work across brands and various internal teams.
• A passion for the toy industry, children’s products, or entertainment marketing is a plus!

Salary:

$110,000.00 - 140,000.00 /year

What You'll Do

Spotter's mission is to give creators access to tools, knowledge, community, and capital so their creativity can change the world. The Senior Data Analyst - Marketing Analytics plays a vital role in that mission by leading analysis and the quantitative strategy for the funnel of our Spotter Studio business. You will work closely with our marketing and product growth teams to surface key insights about user behavior, funnel dynamics and marketing channel effectiveness to shape the future of Spotter's game-changing tools and services for creators.

Responsibilities
• Build out marketing analytics for the Spotter Studio business
• Develop and implement customer segmentation using advanced analytics techniques, such as clustering, predictive modeling, and classification and regression trees to identify actionable insights and improve targeted marketing efforts
• Collaborate with marketing and product growth teams to establish measurement tools, document and communicate measurement logic, and democratize availability of product performance data
• Influence and establish strategies based on insights from our data
• Develop and maintain dashboards and reporting tools to track marketing performance, monitor key metrics, communicate insights and give recommendations to stakeholders
• Constantly monitor these metrics, investigating anomalies, coming up with theories and sharing insights and finding
• Partner with product, marketing and engineering to design measurement into new feature releases during requirements stage, prep and QA reports prior to launch, and follow up after launch

• Support data-driven decision-making processes, advocating for the use of analytics and empirical evidence in product decision-making

• Excellent communication and storytelling skills for technical and non-technical audiences
• Strong proficiency using SQL and/or Python / R for ad-hoc analysis

Why Spotter

title: Data Analyst

description:
Position Summary:

The Data Analyst position is responsible for a wide range of analyses and evaluation activities to support regional operations and targeted initiatives at Regal Medical Group/Lakeside Community.

Under the direction of the Senior Manager of Case Management, the Data Analyst coordinates the preparation of datasets and analyzes data relevant to regional, business, and program operations for all RMG/LMG campuses and initiatives.

The Data Analyst will collaborate closely with executive leadership, operations, and program staff to complete process and outcome evaluations and conduct comprehensive data analyses to quantify the impact of existing and prospective services on the quality of care and healthcare utilization.

Essential Duties and Responsibilities include the following:
• Understanding statistical methods and techniques for data interpretation.
• Proficiency in tools like Smart Sheets to create clear visual representations of data.
• Knowledge of databases and experience working with large datasets.
• Advanced skills in Excel for data manipulation, analysis, and reporting.
• Ensuring the preparation of datasets for analysis.
• Techniques for preprocessing data to ensure accuracy and usability.
• Understanding basic machine learning concepts and algorithms can be beneficial.
• Familiarity with data warehousing concepts and tools.
• Conducting comprehensive data analysis using various statistical methods and tests, including all forms of regression.
• Selecting and utilizing appropriate evaluation and statistical methodologies.
• Identifying and quantifying the impact of existing and prospective services on healthcare utilization and hospital admission reduction.
• Analyzing, reviewing, forecasting, and presenting information for programmatic, operational, and business planning.
• Working with campus and department leadership to develop, coordinate, and implement data evaluation activities.
• Responsible for data review, auditing, aggregation, and analysis across various business units.
• Identifying and quantifying the impact of existing and prospective services through data-driven research and analysis of data and business processes.
• Producing reports that outline various aspects of evaluation and analytics.

description:
Your Role

The Health Data Transformation & Evaluation team drives implementation of the Digital Health Record (DHR). As the business driver, the team leads the integration of various data sources into a longitudinal patient record. The Data Analyst-Health, Principal, will report to Sr. Manager, Health Data Strategy. In this role you will oversee, as a Business Product Owner, the design, development, testing, and deployment of the Digital Health Record, ensuring that it meets Blue Shield’s data-driven objectives. In addition, this role will lead efforts to validate accuracy and integrity of data received from DHR sources and its adoption within the operational workflows by end-users.

Your Work

In this role, you will:
• Liaise with cross functional teams of data architects, modelers and data quality analysts, who are responsible for building the Digital Health Record within the enterprise data warehouse
• Define and implement the data integration strategy, architecture, standards, and best practices for the Digital Health Record, ensuring alignment with the organization's vision, mission, and goals
• Establish and monitor the data quality and governance processes and perform user acceptance testing for the Digital Health Record, ensuring that the data is accurate, complete, consistent, and trustworthy
• Collaborate with stakeholders and business users across the enterprise to understand their data needs and expectations, and to deliver solutions that enable data-driven decision making and insights
• Lead design, analysis, and interpretation of various data sources to meet health data strategy goals including but not limited to creation of Digital Health Record
• Serve as a partner to the Director, Health Data Strategy and Evaluation team to ensure all Digital Health Record and Program evaluation data needs are met

Your Knowledge and Experience
• Requires an MPH, MBA, MS, MA in science, social science, public health, MIS, computer science, data science, health services research or business, or BA/BS with demonstrated equivalent work experience
• Requires 10 years of prior relevant experience, with at least 5 years of in Health Care (managed care, academic, or government payer)
• Proficiency and experience in health informatics is preferred
• Familiarity with health information exchanges, interoperability, longitudinal patient records and meaningful use is preferred
• Experience validating the quality and integrity of incoming data is preferred
• Prior experience in data analysis and reporting, such as SQL, BI tools, and data visualization is preferred
• Experience in Agile and DevOps methodologies, such as Scrum, Kanban, CI/CD, and Git is preferred
• Excellent communication, presentation, and interpersonal skills, with the ability to communicate complex technical concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences
• Strong problem-solving, analytical, and critical thinking skills, with the ability to deliver solutions that meet business objectives and requirements

Pay Range:

The pay range for this role is: $136,400.00 to $204,600.00 for California.

Note:

Please note that this range represents the pay range for this and many other positions at Blue Shield that fall into this pay grade. Blue Shield salaries are based on a variety of factors, including the candidate's experience, location (California, Bay area, or outside California), and current employee salaries for similar roles.

About the position

The Data Analyst Senior position within the Client Data Domain at City National Bank (CNB) is a pivotal role that focuses on data governance, ensuring compliance with regulations set forth by the Office of the Comptroller of the Currency (OCC) and the Federal Reserve Board (FRB). As a Subject Matter Expert, the incumbent will be responsible for critical data elements, data lineage, and data controls, guiding the development and design of data quality testing. This role will report directly to the Data Governance Manager and will involve collaboration with CNB and Royal Bank of Canada (RBC) Enterprise Data Governance to enhance the institution's data governance program. The Banking and Investment Services Division, where this role is situated, plays a crucial part in executing the strategic vision of banking operations. The division's professionals work closely with various business lines to perform essential functions such as client servicing, contact center operations, payments processing, and trade and lending operations. They are also tasked with identifying and mitigating risks while striving to transform support models through automation and advanced digital technologies, ultimately aiming to provide an exceptional experience for clients and businesses. In this role, the Data Analyst Senior will assist in identifying and analyzing critical data elements related to the data domains for which Banking and Investment Services holds accountability. Responsibilities include preparing and analyzing quarterly data quality reports, rolling out CNB's Data Governance reporting and strategy structure, and supporting data remediation initiatives in collaboration with stakeholders. The position also requires attending meetings with various data governance groups and Subject Matter Experts from RBC and Enterprise Risk Management (ERM), ensuring that all required training and special projects are completed successfully.

Responsibilities
• Assist in the identification and analysis of critical data elements related to data domains.
,
• Prepare and analyze quarterly data quality reports, including data compilation and business line reviews.
,
• Roll out CNB's Data Governance reporting and strategy structure, covering various aspects such as Data Quality and Control and Master Data Management.
,
• Conduct overall analysis of results, training, project plan development, and documentation of findings.
,
• Support and/or lead data remediation initiatives in collaboration with stakeholders.
,
• Attend meetings with data governance groups and Subject Matter Experts from RBC and ERM.
,
• Complete all required training and special projects as requested.

Requirements
• Bachelor's Degree or equivalent.
,
• Minimum 6 years of experience in a data analysis role.
,
• Minimum 5 years of experience with SAS or SQL, or other data management and reporting tools.
,
• Minimum 3-5 years of experience in banking/operations.
,
• Excellent interpersonal, verbal, and written communication skills.
,
• Working knowledge of bank processes and controls, especially in client onboarding/offboarding and KYC.
,
• Experience in a formal risk controls environment with a strong understanding of scheduled deliverables.
,
• Ability to work in a collaborative/team-focused environment, communicating directly with managers and peers.
,
• Proficiency in Microsoft Office products including Word, Excel, Visio, and PowerPoint.

• Emphasis in Regulatory Reporting experience preferred.

,
• Comprehensive benefits package including health insurance, retirement plans, and paid time off.
,
