description:
Title:
C-5M Maintenance Data Analyst

Belong, Connect, Grow, with KBR!

Program Summary

The C-5M Super Galaxy is a strategic heavy airlift cargo aircraft providing heavy and outsized cargo transit for the United States Air Force (USAF). The Air Force Life Cycle Management Center (AFLCMC) C-5M Super Galaxy Division (AFLCMC/WLS) is responsible for the development, procurement, and integration of modernized capabilities and for the sustainment and life cycle management of the aircraft. The KBR C-5M team provides support to the C-5M Super Galaxy Division, facilitating the development, implementation, and execution of modernization and sustainment activities related to the Reliability, Maintainability, Quality, Supportability, and Interoperability (RMQSI) of the C-5M weapon system. The KBR C-5M team primarily is co-located with the C-5M Super Galaxy Division at Robins Air Force Base (AFB), Georgia.

Job Summary

The incumbent of this position will function as a key C-5M Maintenance Analyst specialist responsible for logistics integration maintenance data collection and analysis support. The individual will work with the Logistics, Engineering and Program Management teams and perform maintenance data analyst to assist with the Government with planning, managing, and coordination of C-5M life-cycle logistics support. This individual will serve as a C-5M Maintenance Data Analyst, assisting the C-5M Super Galaxy Division with evaluation, enhancement and execution of its Logistics Support Integration activities. They may work in collaborative efforts with System Program Office (SPO), Major Operating Commands (MAJCOMs), field level maintenance personnel, Original Equipment Manufacturers (OEMs) and Defense Logistics Agency (DLA personnel in the development and evaluation of solutions aimed at increasing C-5M Materiel Availability objectives. The incumbent will apply Air Force and/or DoD maintenance and systems knowledge and experience to perform various tasks related to planning, development, implementation, and management of a comprehensive, affordable, and effective system support strategy.

Roles and Responsibilities
• Drafts instructions, support development of various sustainment and project parts lists, performing maintenance data collection and analysis related to supply chain issues, and performing root cause analysis for maintenance and sustainment issues
• Accomplishes historical research for all C-5M aircraft systems, malfunction analysis, modification, parts replacement, components repair, standards, and specifications. Work individually to form solutions with little to no guidance, performing all duties on-time and on-budget, identifying barriers, briefing leadership on deviations, and submitting solutions.
• Performs maintenance data trend analysis, failure mode and effects analysis updates, preventative maintenance package task updates, isolate and analyze aircraft functional system deficiencies, identify appropriate solutions, and assist in the production of data required to implement the improvements.
• Recommends maintenance procedural changes and submits change recommendation documentation via change request channels. Prepare, edit, and/or submit research, travel, technical and other reports,. Evaluate customer submitted: document change requests, deficiency reports, safety/hazard reports, and accident/incident reports to evaluate failure modes and formulate solutions.
• Execution of responsibilities will require key logistics skills, including: problem solving; critical and creative thinking; conflict resolution; multi-tasking; clear and well-organized communication skills (written, verbal and active listening); strong computer skills and proficiency with Microsoft office applications; and the ability to develop well-organized and credible presentations and formal written documents
• Creates appropriate charts and graphs to record results; prepares and/or conducts presentations and briefings to Air Force stakeholders primarily in the C-5M Division.
• Ability to travel out of local area 5-10% of calendar year if needed.
• Candidate must possess the ability to work well as part of a team and with minimal supervision.

Basic Qualifications
• At least 4 to 7 years of experience directly related to the position
• Bachelors Degree in logistics, management, business administration or related field. Note – Additional experience may be considered sufficient to satisfy the degree requirement
• Experience in USAF organizations performing maintenance tasks and functions and demonstrating knowledge of current USAF supply, logistics and maintenance processes, policies and procedure
• Must possess a Secret security clearance or higher
• Must be a US citizen

Preferred Qualifications
• 15+ years experience in USAF and/or DoD logistics and supply systems operations
• 5 years of experience in C-5M maintenance roles, demonstrating a progression to higher levels of experience and proficiency
• Experience supporting the C-5M at Air Force organizational levels
• Experience supporting DoD ACAT I/II/III acquisition programs
• USAF program office experience
• Relevant DAWIA certifications in logistics
• Experience at multiple Air Force or DoD centers and geographic locations

KBR Benefits

KBR offers a selection of competitive lifestyle benefits which could include 401K plan with company match, medical, dental, vision, life insurance, AD&D, flexible spending account, disability, paid time off, or flexible work schedule. We support career advancement through professional training and development.

Belong, Connect and Grow at KBR

At KBR, we are passionate about our people and our Zero Harm culture. These inform all that we do and are at the heart of our commitment to, and ongoing journey toward being a People First company. That commitment is central to our team of team’s philosophy and fosters an environment where everyone can Belong, Connect and Grow. We Deliver – Together.

KBR is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, disability, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, age, national origin, veteran status, genetic information, union status and/or beliefs, or any other characteristic protected by federal, state, or local law.

description:
Company Overview

With 80,000 customers across 150 countries, UKG is the largest U.S.-based private software company in the world. And we’re only getting started. Ready to bring your bold ideas and collaborative mindset to an organization that still has so much more to build and achieve? Read on.

At UKG, you get more than just a job. You get to work with purpose. Our team of U Krewers are on a mission to inspire every organization to become a great place to work through our award-winning HR technology built for all.

Here, we know that you’re more than your work. That’s why our benefits help you thrive personally and professionally, from wellness programs and tuition reimbursement to U Choose — a customizable expense reimbursement program that can be used for more than 200+ needs that best suit you and your family, from student loan repayment, to childcare, to pet insurance. Our inclusive culture, active and engaged employee resource groups, and caring leaders value every voice and support you in doing the best work of your career. If you’re passionate about our purpose — people —then we can’t wait to support whatever gives you purpose. We’re united by purpose, inspired by you.

Join a lean, fast-paced enterprise data & analytics team at the center of advancing our company’s data-driven culture. As a Business Data Analyst for Data & Analytics, you’ll bring your business acumen, sharp analytical skills and strong technical expertise to design, develop and deliver enterprise-wide data solutions and insights that enables exceptional customer experience, exceptional employee experience and continued profitable growth.

As a Lead Business Data Analyst for Data & Analytics, you will be accountable not only for the end-to-end design and delivery of complex data solutions ensuring their quality, reliability, and performance but also for mentoring peers and ensuring there’s alignment with strategic goals. This role requires strong collaboration cross-functionally with business stakeholders (Sales, Marketing, Relationship Management, Finance, Services, HR and Legal), Solution Managers, Data Scientists, Software Engineers and other team members to drive impactful results and accelerate our company’s growth.

The right individual will put our customers first, elevate their peers, be curious, open-minded, resourceful, collaborative, proactive, a critical analytical thinker, and be relentless in pursuit of desired outcomes.

Responsibilities

Business Understanding: Deeply understand our business, systems, and data to develop solutions that solve complex business problems, meet stakeholder needs and accelerate their path to value.

Stakeholder Relationships and Management: Build strong relationships with senior stakeholders to understand their business objectives and pain points fostering collaborative partnerships across the business. Provide clear communication to team members and business stakeholders related to requirements, issues, and solution delivery. Own and lead UAT sessions as well as business demos of new features and stories.

Solution Development: Own the end-to-end technical design and development of scalable, reliable, and maintainable data & analytic solutions such as reports, metrics, scorecards, dashboards, KPIs, and self-service datasets that are widely adopted and drive action across the business.

User Story Development: Transform business requirements into detailed functional requirements and document user stories following best practices. This includes writing clear acceptance criteria and definition of done for each story.

Agile Practices: Work collaboratively as part of a scrum team and use Agile methodology to build and deliver solutions, ensuring efficient and effective development cycles.

Collaboration: Collaborate with Business Stakeholders, Software Engineers, Data Scientists, Architects, Technical Project Managers, Enablement, and other Business Data Analysts to execute various strategic programs.

Mentorship: Provide technical mentorship and guidance to junior Business Data Analysts, fostering a culture of learning and growth mindset. Provide input to business stakeholders on potential improvements to help transform UKG's business operations.

Documentation and Knowledge Sharing: Lead efforts to document features, enhancements, and fixes thoroughly, contributing to training materials and knowledge transfer across teams. Promote proper interpretation of data and analytics results to educate and support self-service business intelligence.

Quality Assurance and Testing: Build testable analytic solutions, oversee the definition and execution of test cases, provide solution demonstrations, and lead user testing sessions and black box testing, when applicable, that result in user acceptance as well as black box testing.

Opportunity Identification: Identify strategic opportunities and communicate recommendations to senior leaders that can improve feature adoption, increase revenue, decrease costs, and/or mitigate risks across the business.

Innovation: Be a thought leader and stay current with emerging technologies (ex. Generative AI) and industry trends, championing their adoption to drive innovation and productivity enhancements within Digital and across the business.

Success Metrics: Lead the creation of success metrics and measurement processes to track benefits on project work.

Required Qualifications

Experience: 8+ years of data analytics work experience.

Business Acumen: Strong business acumen with 5+ years of business experience in a large corporate environment.

Leadership: Proven experience leading teams and managing large-scale projects.

Technical Skills: Advanced SQL skills with 3+ years of experience in SQL and Relational Database systems; ability to write queries against large data warehouses (such as Google BigQuery, Microsoft Azure, Oracle) and understand efficient aggregation and display principles.

BI Proficiency: Advanced proficiency with BI platforms (Power BI, Tableau, etc.) with 3+ years of report building and analysis.

Analytical Skills: Proven analytical and problem-solving skills; process-oriented and metrics-driven.

Data Visualization: Advanced knowledge of data visualization techniques.

Communication: Excellent verbal and written communication skills with the ability to interact professionally with a diverse group of executives, managers, and subject matter experts.

Teamwork: Works effectively within a team, under pressure and tight deadlines, while being well-organized.

Adaptability: Flexible and adaptive to change, open-minded, curious, resourceful, and has a positive attitude.

Preferred Qualifications

Business Analysis: Extensive experience in business analysis, including leading complex business requirements gathering and translating them into technical solutions.

Cloud Technologies: Experience with Cloud technologies (Azure and Google Cloud).

Enterprise Applications: Strong understanding of various enterprise applications (e.g., ERP, CRM, HRIS) and the ability to leverage these systems effectively to deliver robust data solutions.

Data Product Development: Proven expertise in developing data products for cross-functional teams to self-serve insights.

Software Development: Familiarity with software development practices, including code reviews, testing, and DevOps.

Where we’re going

UKG is on the cusp of something truly special. Worldwide, we already hold the #1 market share position for workforce management and the #2 position for human capital management. Tens of millions of frontline workers start and end their days with our software, with billions of shifts managed annually through UKG solutions today. Yet it’s our AI-powered product portfolio designed to support customers of all sizes, industries, and geographies that will propel us into an even brighter tomorrow!

We are seeking a Consulting Clinical Data Analyst for our team to ensure that we continue to provide all patients with high quality, efficient care. Did you get into our industry for these reasons? We are an amazing team that works hard to support each other and are seeking a phenomenal addition like you who feels patient care is as meaningful as we do. We want you to apply!
Job Summary and Qualifications

The Consulting Clinical Data Analyst of Accelerated Technologies and Innovation plays a crucial role in defining and executing the AI and Data-driven product innovation with a strong emphasis on emerging technologies, rapid development, and cloud computing. This individual will partner with product managers, data engineers, ML engineers and Data scientist, software architect and related teams working on various innovative projects across the organization. This role requires a strong understanding of technical aspects, excellent communication skills, and the ability to foster collaboration and innovation within the team. You will work with a mixture of resource types to build teams to perform the activities listed with special focus on establishing a pod like structure of resources through staffing vendors that can be assigned to different efforts.

The ideal candidate must have clinical data domain knowledge, medical terminology, FHIR/HL7 standard and code should able to adept at handling multiple projects concurrently, ensuring alignment with organizational strategic initiatives, and managing resources effectively. A strong emphasis is placed on maintaining excellent working relationships with other teams, leaders, subject-matter experts, and business partners within the enterprise.

Major Responsibilities:
• Establish challenging goals, plans and objectives that support the data innovation.
• Manage relationships and serve as primary point of contact for data related
• Clean, analyze, and visualize a variety of Clinical, patient financial and operation event data domain based on requirement
• Develop automated dynamic report to support key business initiatives to improve clinical operation
• Guide business leaders with confidence in your analytics output to ensure smooth execution
• Summarize and present data innovation techniques, analysis, assumptions and results.
• Lead and support day-to-day operations and tracking.

description:
Overview

The Senior Data & Analytics Lead will drive the business and data strategy within our Business Intelligence team. The individual will lead a team of analysts and data visualization experts, partnering closely with channel and strategy teams to deliver high-impact insights that inform and guide strategic decisions. With a strong advertising agency background, the ideal candidate will use their expertise to enhance client storytelling, develop scalable analytics frameworks, and deliver actionable data that drives business growth.

This in-person role allows candidates to choose their preferred location from our three offices: Birmingham, AL, Mobile, AL, or Nashville, TN.
• Reports to: Vice President of Strategy and Research

Qualifications
• 7-10 years minimum experience in data analytics, business intelligence, or a related field, with a focus on advertising or marketing.
• Proven leadership experience managing teams in a collaborative environment.
• Expertise in developing and executing data strategies aligned with business objectives.
• Advanced knowledge of data visualization tools (e.g., Tableau, Power BI) and analytical software (e.g., SQL, Python, R).
• Strong background in translating complex data into clear, actionable insights.
• Excellent communication skills, with the ability to present data-driven recommendations to clients and internal teams.
• Bachelor’s degree in a relevant field; advanced degree preferred.

Responsibilities
• Develop and execute comprehensive data strategy plans that align with clients’ overall business goals.
• Partner with channel and strategy teams to ensure data insights are aligned with business objectives and drive measurable growth.
• Lead client storytelling and insights presentations, effectively communicating the business impact of data insights to agency leadership and clients.
• Act as a strategic advisor, identifying opportunities where data and analytics can deliver the most value.
• Mentor and manage a team of analysts and data visualization experts, fostering a high-performance culture focused on innovation and collaboration.
• Oversee the ongoing development of analytics and reporting processes, implementing tools and frameworks that enhance efficiency and scalability.
• Design and oversee the production of reporting frameworks that provide actionable insights into campaign and channel performance, tailored to specific business strategies.
• Collaborate with Client Engagement teams to develop and communicate key performance indicators (KPIs) that support proactive decision-making.

Success Factors

Technical Skills:
• Expertise in data visualization tools such as Tableau or Power BI.
• Proficiency in SQL, Python, R, or other analytical software.
• Strong understanding of marketing and advertising analytics.
• Ability to design scalable reporting frameworks and processes.

Leadership Skills:
• Proven ability to lead, mentor, and develop high-performing teams.
• Strategic mindset with a focus on aligning data insights with business goals.
• Collaborative approach to working with cross-functional teams.

Soft Skills:
• Excellent storytelling and presentation skills.
• Strong problem-solving abilities with a proactive mindset.
• Ability to manage multiple projects and priorities in a fast-paced environment.
• High emotional intelligence and adaptability to different client needs and industries.

The Senior Data & Analytics Lead will play a critical role in driving the success of our Business Intelligence team and enhancing the value we deliver to our clients. If you are passionate about data, strategy, and leadership within the advertising industry, we encourage you to apply.

At Lewis, we are dedicated to building a diverse, inclusive, and authentic workplace, so if you're excited about this role, but your past experience aligns differently with some qualifications in the job description, we encourage you to apply anyway. You may be just the right candidate for this or other roles.

description:
Sage is seeking a Business Intelligence Data Analyst to join its growing Global Routes to Revenue (“RTR”) Planning team. The RTR team is responsible for GTM planning and design, developing commercial models, revenue planning and creating an analytical framework to measure GTM performance.
The Business Intelligence Data Analyst will assist across the Planning, Performance and Analytics pillars within the wider team. The successful candidate will have high levels of curiosity and be extremely willing to learn about commercial drivers and models across the business. They will also be used to working with data in an agile environment and be a confident presenter.

We look for candidates who have some pre-existing expertise and supplement this with in-house training and experience to develop professionals of the highest caliber, who can bridge the gap between commercial drivers in finance, marketing, and operations.

Key Responsibilities
• Ad hoc commercial modelling and analysis to assist with performance analysis and reviews
• Work closely with stakeholders across the business to produce high quality analyses that drive actionable insights
• Communicate findings, insights, and results in a clear, concise, and effective manner to senior management
• Establish strong relationships with and become a key advisor to Sage’s GTM executives
• Work effectively in diverse teams with an inclusive team culture where people are recognized for their contribution and support each other to learn and prosper.
• Partner with finance, sales, and marketing teams to gain a rich understanding of business processes, analytics and reporting needs and gaps
• Work on a global planning model for key Business Units across Sage and engaging with regional commercial teams to utilize these models.

Qualifications
• 1-2 years in a business reporting or analytics role, including using technology/tools for reporting and dashboard insights (SQL experience required, Power BI experience a plus)
• Ability to manipulate, analyze and visualize data into value-add deep-dive analyses
• Understanding of financial and commercial business drivers/KPIs
• Proven analytical skills and systematic problem solving
• Demonstrated ability to work with others effectively in teams and being able to work under own initiative under tight timeframes
• Strong communication skills, with the ability to simplify and explain complex problems to stakeholders

For this role, in those locations, the target salary range for new hires is: $85,000 to $100,000.

description:
The Data Analyst, Data & Analytics will be a key TSP Data Strategy and Analytics team member. The incumbent will be responsible for helping drive the successful execution of the TSP Data Strategy to enable the organization to make better decisions thru clean, consistent, and understandable data.

This position is remote anywhere within the US and Canada.

They will be working on various aspects of data projects and business projects that have a data component. This role documents, designs, delivers and maintains complex data analytics solutions. This is to be accomplished by adhering to TSP data architecture governance and standards to ensure a high-quality analysis is maintained throughout. The incumbent will constantly update the practices to enhance the evolution of our data ecosystem.

This position will work directly with Operations and Supply Chain groups. They will be supporting several different teams such as Project Management, Customer Service, Manufacturing and Installations.

Reporting
This position will be reporting to the Director, Data Analytics and Integrations.
Key Functions
• Act as an SME on the data needs across multiple business teams (Supply Chain, Operations, Project Management)
• Support the transition of Domo reporting assets into Power BI
• Develop data insight solutions that help the business determine the next course of action
• Produce standard daily/weekly/monthly reports on KPIs and metrics
• Generate customized analysis and reporting, examining the effectiveness of TSP
• Work with other data professionals to define and enhance the data layer (Lake, DWH)
• Act as a liaison between business and technical audiences
• Active member in the process improvements for the Data Analytics team at TSP
• Define and document data dependencies and data flow diagrams of the solution developed

Qualifications
• Strong analytical, communication, and teamwork abilities
• Ability to work effectively under pressure and in rapidly changing environments
• 3 years of experience working with Power BI as an Analyst Professional.
• Experience with other visualization tools like Domo, Tableau or Looker
• 2+ Years of Experience with Excel at the advanced level, and some familiarity with power query. Examples are Vlookup, Index+Match, Sumifs, Conditional Logic, and Data cleaning
• 5 years of experience in a data-related role in a large company
• 2 years of experience gathering requirements from business stakeholders
• Expert knowledge in SQL to gather, clean, and analyze data
• Knowledge of SQL Server and Snowflake is preferred

What We Offer
• A commitment that Safety is #1
• Competitive benefits, pay, and retirement plan options!
• Career growth, stability, and flexible work arrangements.

Responsible Manufacturing – Protecting Our Planet for the Future

With a history of 140 years, Tarkett is a worldwide leader in innovative flooring and sport surface solutions with 12,000 employees and 34 industrial sites. Offering a wide range of products including vinyl, linoleum, rubber, carpet, wood, laminate, artificial turf, and athletic tracks. The Group serves customers in more than 100 countries across the globe.

Committed to change the game with circular economy and to reducing its carbon footprint, the Group has implemented an eco-innovation strategy based on Cradle to Cradle® principles, fully aligned with its Tarkett Human-Conscious Design® approach.

description:
We are hiring a Senior Data Analyst, Crisis & Resilience as a part of our Enterprise Resilience and Crisis Management (ERCM) Team. In an era marked by unprecedented global challenges, the significance of resilience and crisis management cannot be overstated. The world's interconnectedness has amplified the impacts of crises, be they economic downturns, natural disasters, pandemics, or socio-political upheavals. Resilience empowers organizations to adapt, recover, and flourish despite these adversities. It fosters a proactive mindset, where anticipation, preparation, and swift response to crises are paramount. Furthermore, effective crisis management ensures that when disruptions occur, there are structured strategies in place to mitigate damage, facilitate recovery, and sustain operations. Together, resilience and crisis management form the backbone of a robust response framework, enhancing our ability to navigate and thrive in an increasingly complex and dynamic global landscape.

The Enterprise Resilience and Crisis Management (ERCM) Team is hiring a Senior Data Analyst who’ll have the opportunity to own and architect the end-to-end data lifecycle for crisis and resilience analytics. Day to day you will work closely with our business stakeholders to learn about their business and understand their data and analytics challenges. Additionally, you will work with our current Analytics team to help manage our Azure Resources and work with other engineering teams to source and ingest data, model, and prepare data for analysis and usage. Finally, you’ll work with ERCM team members to deliver insights on risks to help drive crisis and resilience stakeholders across the enterprise.

The Senior Data Analyst, Crisis & Resilience will be skilled at leveraging data as a strategic asset and can map analyses to areas of risk for action; has a record of accomplishment in developing data analyses that address risks or performance, collaborating and influencing across teams to develop key performance indicators, coordinating multiple timelines, and managing complex, cross discipline projects. The Senior Data Analyst, Crisis & Resilience should be agile and able to adapt to support an ever-changing company, evolving technology stack, and shifting risk environment; leads by example and fosters an open work environment where cross-collaboration, inclusiveness, and diversity of perspective are valued.

In alignment with our Microsoft values, we are committed to cultivating an inclusive work environment for all employees to positively impact our culture every day.

Microsoft’s mission is to empower every person and every organization on the planet to achieve more. As employees we come together with a growth mindset, innovate to empower others, and collaborate to realize our shared goals. Each day we build on our values of respect, integrity, and accountability to create a culture of inclusion where everyone can thrive at work and beyond.  

#CELA

Responsibilities
• Build scalable data assets (dashboards, underlying data sets, and workflows) to unlock reliable and high velocity decision support
• Contribute to and manage the Azure infrastructure (e.g., Azure Data Lake Storage, Azure SQL, Azure Synapse, Kusto/Azure Data Explorer, Power BI, Azure Log Analytics, Data Flows, Fabric)
• Perform analyses using a variety of analytical tools (SQL, Python, Azure Databricks, Synapse, Power BI, Fabric etc), execute analyses and interpret results with actionable recommendations, and partners to build on others’ frameworks.
• Problem solve with crisis and resilience SMEs and do deep dive data analyses on their data flows, requirements and ideate data solutions
• Continually ensure both security and privacy are paramount in the ways that Enterprise Resilience and Crisis Management (ERCM) stewards the data that it has access to.

Other
• Embody our culture and values

Qualifications

Required Qualifications
• Bachelor's Degree in Statistics, Mathematics, Analytics, Data Science, Engineering, Computer Science, Business, Economics or related field AND 4+ years experience in data analysis and reporting, data science, business intelligence, or business and financial analysis
• OR Master's Degree in Mathematics, Analytics, Data Science, Engineering, Computer Science, Business, Economics or related field AND 2+ years experience in data analysis and reporting, data science, business intelligence, or business and financial analysis
• OR equivalent experience.
• 4+ years experience working in a data intensive environment and translating business needs into data requirements
• 2+ years experience Microsoft Azure stack, SQL, Python, Azure Databricks, Synapse, Power BI, Fabric, and/or Machine Learning and AI

Preferred Qualifications
• Bachelor's Degree in Statistics, Mathematics, Analytics, Data Science, Engineering, Computer Science, Business, Economics or related field AND 6+ years experience in data analysis and reporting, data science, business intelligence, or business and financial analysis
• OR Master's Degree in Mathematics, Analytics, Data Science, Engineering, Computer Science, Business, Economics or related field AND 4+ years experience in data analysis and reporting, data science, business intelligence, or business and financial analysis
• OR equivalent experience.
• 6+ years of demonstrated experience working in a data intensive environment and translating business needs into data requirements (experience with Microsoft Azure stack, SQL, Python, Azure Databricks, Synapse, Power BI, Fabric, Machine Learning and AI).
• 3+ years crisis management and resilience experience working in a large multinational organization.
• 3+ years experience collaborating effectively with PMs, non-technical team members, and other technical SMEs as well as across teams to define and implement sustainable solutions.
• 3+ years experience leading cross-functional and/or cross-team projects.

Data Analytics IC4 - The typical base pay range for this role across the U.S. is USD $103,800 - $200,300 per year. There is a different range applicable to specific work locations, within the San Francisco Bay area and New York City metropolitan area, and the base pay range for this role in those locations is USD $133,700 - $219,200 per year.

description:
We’re looking for a Staff Analyst to join the Mailchimp Marketing Analytics team. You will be responsible for owning key analyses, projects, reporting, and processes leading to insights that help attract new customers and drive revenue growth.

As a Staff Analyst on the Marketing Analytics team, you will help lead strategic, data-driven decision making at Mailchimp. In this role, you will conduct a variety of analyses to understand and explain customer behavior, business trends, and predict future outcomes. The focus of this role is to drive improvements in the conversion funnel for our prospect-facing website through a focus on rigorous experimentation, strategic deep dives and robust reporting.
Responsibilities
• Build experimentation plans to robustly isolate impact of website changes, and guide future strategy for key initiatives
• Deep dive into customer data to understand where growth is coming from and how it can be replicated
• Profile customer segment to identify how the website experience can be tailored to their needs
• Analyze short, medium, and long-term impact of pricing and promotion changes on customer acquisition
• Explore alternative methodologies for statistical inference to identify and size the impact of web initiatives
• Design insightful and actionable dashboards to guide web decision making
• Craft narratives and recommendations from analyses, build presentations, and present findings to business stakeholders

Functional
• Deep understanding of web analytics data and event tracking (Google Analytics experience is strongly preferred)
• Broad experience deploying website experiments across optimization levers (copy testing, page re-builds, audiences, promotions, pricing), test designs (A/B, Factorial, Sequential, etc) and inference (Frequentist, Bayesian)
• Expertise with funnel and cohort analysis to prioritize initiatives and guide strategy
• Experience in partnering with and presenting to executive and cross-functional leadership
• Strong communication, collaboration, and problem-solving abilities

Technical
• Advanced knowledge of SQL and experience working with cloud-based data warehouses (Google Big Query preferred)
• Proven experience in stitching together disparate data sources and building data infrastructure, defining KPIs, and tracking business performance
• Experience with business case modeling and opportunity sizing
• Demonstrated experience with data visualization tools (Tableau) and dashboard development for executive teams

Work/Education
• Minimum of 5 year’s experience in an analytics-focused role. Prior work experience within a SaaS company is preferred
• Bachelor’s or Graduate degree in a technical subject; equivalent experience will be considered

Applies a comprehensive understanding of end-to-end data processes/flows and concepts to implement frameworks, processes, controls, models, and solutions to ensure data is effectively managed across the organization or within a specific business unit. Reviews reports to identify data integrity issues and provides feedback to application/database administrators to ensure any issues are addressed. Answers questions from end-users of reports to provide additional context. Reporting may be focused on regulatory matters, operational metrics, and productivity metrics. Responsible for maintaining the integrity of data during the transfer from source systems into business unit data assets Applies a comprehensive understanding of data processes/flows and concepts to implement frameworks, processes, controls, models, and solutions for business unit. Be able to set the standards / apply data for fit for use when applying data into business decisions. Drives out the identification and mitigation of data issues as necessary to support organization priorities. Identifies and champions the implementation of data process and practice improvements. Lead automation for all deliverables with process efficiency and effectiveness.

ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES

Following is a summary of the essential functions for this job. Other duties may be performed, both major and minor, which are not mentioned below. Specific activities may change from time to time.
• Lead business analysis efforts for projects related to finance and regulatory reporting. Using SAS , SQL etc. , conduct exploratory data analysis, data profiling, investigate data errors, generate ad-hoc reports, validate data as part of user acceptance testing.
• Partner with technology and architecture team for system functionality enhancements , research, analyze, design, and/or maintain data sources in information systems in support of projects, information needs, and changing requirements
• Apply deep understanding of data integration process and participate in large/complex data warehouse initiatives, design discussions, and prototype review.
• Perform analysis, validation and interpretation of reporting outputs.
• Responsible for identifying Critical data elements, developing business rules, reconciliation checks, measuring data quality. Identify the data quality issues and data gaps in the current organization environment, analyze the root cause for data issues and provide data quality improvement solutions.
• Work with Regulatory reporting team and help translate reporting instructions into functional business requirements.
• Uses sophisticated analytical thought to exercise judgment and identify innovative solutions.
• Applies a comprehensive understanding of how the organization operates to solve technical, operational, and business problems.

QUALIFICATIONS

Required Qualifications:

The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge, skill and/or ability required. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.
• Bachelor's degree and 5+ years of related experience or an equivalent combination of education and experience.
• Deep specialized and/or broad knowledge within a professional discipline.
• Sound and comprehensive understanding of business and organizational strategies and processes.
• Ability to interpret internal and external business challenges and implement best practices to improve products, processes, or services.
• Ability to lead projects of significant complexity and risk exposure.
• Ability to exercise judgment in solving technical, operational, and organizational challenges in the context of business objectives and priorities.
• Sophisticated analytical skills and the ability to solve complex technical and business problems.
• Ability to influence others to adopt a new perspective (new automation, new metrics, new tools etc.) Focus on process automation to improve efficiency.
• Knowledge of the industry's competitive landscape and an understanding of the market and regulatory factors that shape the industry.

Preferred Qualifications:
• Master's degree or MBA and 10 years of related experience.
• Previous experience in the banking industry.
• Proficiency with SAS and SQL.
• Experience with Data Integration, Extraction, Transformation, and Loading
• Understanding of Data Management/Governance principles.
• BI reporting experience.

ABOUT US:

Tennessee Hospital Association (THA) is a not-for-profit membership association, to serve as an advocate for hospitals, health systems, and other healthcare organizations and the patients they serve. The Association also provides education and information for its members and informs the public about hospitals and healthcare issues at the state and national levels.

The mission of the Tennessee Center for Patient Safety (TCPS) is to advance Tennessee hospitals’ adoption of proven strategies that enhance the reliability, safety, and quality of care received by patients. The TCPS provides extensive education, resources, and direct support to hospitals to accomplish the mission of better outcomes for patients.

JOB SUMMARY:

The primary responsibility of the Clinical Quality Data Analyst is to support THA and the Tennessee Center for Patient Safety (TCPS) as an expert resource for data analysis and hospital/state performance with THA Hospital Investment Program (HIP) Quality measures, Centers for Medicaid and Medicare Services (CMS) measures, departmental operations, and THA member requests for review and analysis. The Clinical Quality Data Analyst will provide HIP program support through management and coordination of hospital data collection, analysis, feedback, and reporting. This position will report directly to the Director of Quality & Patient Safety Organization (PSO) in TCPS and will work closely with the TCPS Senior Vice President (SVP) and Information Services Department to provide reports and analysis to TCPS staff, member hospitals, and TennCare. The analyst will work with membership by actively engaging members through relevant data reports, benchmarking, and comparisons and interpreting complex clinical data using statistical methods and software tools. Further responsibilities of this position are providing direct support and education to hospitals in data collection, monitoring the completeness and accuracy of reported data, and ensuring compliance with measure definitions under the TennCare HIP Quality Component Program. They will also work with healthcare professionals and TCPS Clinical Quality Improvement Specialists to evaluate patient outcomes and process improvements.

ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS OF THE JOB:

1. The ability to adapt to a changing work environment and meet challenges presented throughout the day.

2. Manage HIP Quality Component measures to meet program deliverables.

3. Organize, analyze, and aggregate hospital and state performance reports through both claims and facility data

4. Design, deploy, and monitor data quality metrics as part of the Hospital Investment Program-Quality Measure Component.

5. Develop and implement processes to monitor data quality and completeness of all routine tasks and special requests. Respond to data and HIP/CMS inquiries quickly to support hospital stakeholders, TennCare, and THA staff.

6. Work collaboratively with THA IT, Director of Quality & PSO, and TennCare development team in communicating needs around the HIP quality database and reporting tools. Collaborate with cross-functional teams to ensure data quality dashboards meet the needs of all stakeholders.

7. Consult and aid in the design and development of reports, visualizations, and analyses.

8. Maintain THA quality measure database for HIP.

9. Create and manage reports and dashboards for TCPS and TennCare specific to CMS and HIP measures. Data graphs include run charts, combo charts, pareto, scatter plots, histograms, and more.

10. Prepare data for presentation to committees, TCPS SVP, TennCare, and THA board of directors to ensure consistent messages from all levels of the organization.

11. Prepare data performance reports for hospitals, in collaboration with TennCare, and meet all applicable deadlines.

12. Serve as the primary point of contact for HIP quality performance reports to ensure timely submission, distribution, and quality incentive payments.

13. Distribute quarterly summary HIP performance reports to monitor progress for each participating hospital.

14. Participate in planning data collection tools for new HIP quality measures and communicate changes in collection and reporting to a broad stakeholder audience.

15. Serve as the liaison for data collection and reporting between TCPS, TennCare, and participating hospitals.

16. Drive automation initiatives to streamline data collection, analysis, and reporting processes, reducing manual efforts and increasing efficiency for participating hospitals.

17. Develop and implement quality control measures to ensure accuracy, completeness, and reliability of data throughout the HIP submission and analysis process. Identify and resolve data quality issues in a timely manner, working closely with internal and external teams.

18. Collaborate with THA IT to design submission fields into the reporting database.

19. Teach participating hospitals on new measures, data submission process, and interpreting performance reports. Education will include hosting virtual office hours and webinars.

20. Maintain the database of member hospital HIP quality component contacts in both the THA member and THA quality measure databases. This includes maintenance of system and data integrity; maintenance of hospital and system information; compilation and customization of reports; defining system needs; and adding, editing, and inactivating users.

21. Understand state and federal reporting requirements in the Center for Disease Control’s National Healthcare Safety Network (NHSN), CMS, and The Joint Commission.

22. Work in collaboration with TCPS Clinical Quality Data Manager to administer and track NHSN reporting, including group rights, data compilation, creation of customized reports, and other quality initiatives.

23. Evaluate CMS and HIP Quality Measures and offer creative ideas to improve performance and workflows.

24. Support internal clinical and quality improvement staff by supplying data reports and trend information as needed.

25. Perform other tasks and duties as assigned by the Director of Quality & PSO and TCPS SVP.

26. Must be available in the office during regular office hours unless job responsibilities require otherwise, or hybrid work arrangement is in place.

27. Travel approximately 5 percent of the time, as necessary to fulfill job responsibilities; must be available for out-of-town travel, be able to drive an automobile, and maintain a valid driver’s license.

DIMENSIONS:

Volume: 170+ hospitals—Working with members and non-members

Number of people supervised (direct reports): 0

GUIDANCE & DIRECTION: (Policies, precedents or procedures that guide this work)

1. TCPS is under the leadership of the TCPS SVP.

2. The THA Board of Directors and THA President and CEO guide the priorities and initiatives of TCPS.

3. The TCPS Quality Committee, Chief Nursing Officer (CNO) Calls, and Chief Medical Officer (CMO) Society may provide input and recommendations to TCPS.

4. The deliverables, HIP agreements, and grants outline the program and outcome expectations.

5. CMS Quality Measures, CDC NHSN, and U. S. Department of Health and Human Services (HHS).

6. Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA).

7. THA Information Security Policies and Procedures.
Requirements:

Educational and Experience Requirements Needed to Perform the Duties of the Job:

1. Requires at least two years of experience working in healthcare, hospitals, public health, or healthcare performance improvement.

2. Bachelor’s degree is preferred in a scientific or related healthcare field including, but not limited to, data analysis, health informatics, epidemiology, statistics, data science, public health, health information management, or business analytics.

OR

Consideration given to candidates with credentials as a Certified Professional in Healthcare Quality (CPHQ), Registered Health Information Technician (RHIT), Registered Health Information Administrator (RHIA), Project Management Professional (PMP), Clinical Informatics, data analytics, or similar certifications in healthcare or public health that also have an associate’s degree.

3. Previous experience working with healthcare teams and familiarity with electronic medical records including, but not limited to, EPIC, Oracle (Cerner), and Meditech.

4. Previous experience working with healthcare claims data.

5. Working knowledge and understanding of clinical classification systems, such as the ICD and Healthcare Common Procedure Coding System (HCPS).

6. Experience working on a team and providing information via email and phone on process activities.

7. Experience in patient safety, clinical performance improvement, data abstraction, or outcomes measurement.

Skills Required to Perform the Duties of the Job:

1. Advanced computer skills–proficiency in Microsoft Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook and Teams; spreadsheets; datasets; charts; and database software, such as SAS, Tableau, and/or SQL.

2. Working experience and knowledge with software like PowerBI, Tableau, and other data statistical and visualization tools.

3. Advanced knowledge of collecting, editing, and charting numerical data.

4. Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to interpret complex datasets and extract meaningful insights.

5. Knowledge of hospital claims data (International Classification Diseases-10 (ICD-10), Diagnosis Related Groups (DRG), and Current Procedural Technology (CPT) codes—medical and coding terminology.

6. Understanding of data science.

7. Strong data management and organizational skills.

8. Ability to work on multiple projects concurrently and effectively handle changes in project requirements.

9. Ability to adhere to a schedule and meet deadlines.

10. Attention to completeness, accuracy, and detail.

11. Ability to handle requests and corrections by staff and members with courtesy and professionalism.

12. Ability to critically think and use independent judgment.

13. Strong interpersonal skills.

14. Work collaboratively within a team.

15. Creativity and vision to organize data in meaningful presentation formats to deliver key messages.

16. Effective written and oral communication skills.

17. Must maintain good working relationships with THA staff, member hospital staffs, and external partners.

CHEP helps move more goods to more people, in more places than any other organization on earth via our 347 million pallets, crates and containers. We employ approximately 13,000 people and operate in 60 countries. Through our pioneering and sustainable share-and-reuse business model, the world's biggest brands trust us to help them transport their goods more efficiently, safely and with less environmental impact.

What does that mean for you? You'll join an international organization big enough to take you anywhere, and small enough to get you there sooner. University Health Network (UHN) is hiring a Data Analyst to work in the growing field of Healthcare Value Based Care. This position offers a work from home option for employees who meet performance requirements. Candidate must reside in East Tennessee Region and be able to commute to the corporate office located in Knoxville, TN for occasional meetings. Candidate must be able to maintain HIPAA privacy requirements when working in a home office setting.

Note: This position is funded through a grant and is expected to continue until December 31, 2026.

University Health Network is a clinically integrated network and manages University Health ACO, LLC (an accountable care organization). We work in partnership with the University of Tennessee Medical Center, University Physicians’ Association (UPA), area physicians, and commercial and Medicare insurance companies. We strive to deliver the healthcare triple aim: Better care for individuals, better health for populations, and lowering growth in expenditures.

The Data Analyst is a full-time position that is responsible for analyzing large sets of data from multiple sources. The Senior level analyst works within a team and serves as technical support for TeleHealth Services. The Senior analyst will mentor junior caregivers providing technical guidance and adherence to best practices. They facilitate regular meetings with customer stakeholders to provide work updates, set project priorities and establish deliverable timelines. They have a deep understanding of the clinical and operating data for the areas they support to ensure the integrity and accuracy of customer data. They drive information insights through data exploration, interpretation, report development and visual storytelling. This role will help manage projects using ServiceNow, including intake, establishing timelines, negotiating customer expectations, and project tracking.

This position is part of a highly skilled, high impact team with deep clinical and technical expertise in leveraging healthcare data to solve real-world problems. Our teams report to senior analytics leaders and work in strong partnership with key business and clinical leaders across all areas of Intermountain Health. This team provides ongoing training, maintenance, monitoring and promotion of data applications and reports to ensure data insights are widely known, accessible, and used to its fullest potential. This position helps develop and deploy world class data analytics at Intermountain Health, one of the nation’s leading health systems. Will partner with business and clinical leaders, and data professionals across the organization, supporting our Mission to help people live the healthiest lives possible.

Partner with Analytic leadership to ensure customer priorities are understood and resourced. description:
Overview

Do you want to build an impactful career to change the world for the better?

If you’re looking for a place to grow your career, where you can contribute to a dynamic consulting firm, tackle challenging project work, and collaborate with industry recognized professionals - Geosyntec is the place for you!

As an Early-Career Environmental Data Analyst/Data Manager in Tampa, Jacksonville, Orlando, or Pensacola, FL, you will be part of our information management practice and work with our team of consulting scientists and engineers in addressing our clients’ data management needs. Initially, this professional will be trained in our standard operating protocols of database architecture, EQuIS and GIS work product preparation, and laboratory analytical data management and validation. The candidate will use this initial training to support our ongoing operations through a focus on database management and other tools to compile, visualize and analyze data from a variety of streaming and static sources; build interactive dashboards and reports; and assist with the design, development, and implementation of new products and services for our clients.

Geosyntec is an innovative, international engineering and consulting firm serving private and public-sector clients to address new ventures and complex problems involving our environment, natural resources, and civil infrastructure. Our engineers, scientists, technical and project employees serve our clients from offices across the world. Ranked by ENR as one of the top environmental engineering design firms, Geosyntec is internationally known for its technical leadership, broad experience, and exceptional client service.

We invest in our people. Each employee is unique, and your career at Geosyntec will be too. We offer competitive pay and benefits, and well-being programs to support you and your family.

To Learn More Visit: http://www.geosyntec.com/careers/.

Essential Duties and Responsibilities
• Interacting with multidisciplinary internal teams and external clients to provide integrated data management and visualization solutions for environmental engineering, and geoscience projects;
• Designing, developing, and managing project-specific relational database applications using desktop and enterprise database software;
• Compiling, processing, verifying, analyzing, visualizing, and reporting large and diverse datasets;
• Automating processes with Python and other scripting languages and platforms (VBA, Microsoft PowerAutomate, etc.);
• Using EQuIS platform and other Microsoft SQL Server based database to manage project data, including extraction, transformation, and loading (ETLs) of data;
• Configuring and implementing EQuIS tools such as customizing EQuIS reports, customizing and deploying EQuIS data loaders, building web dashboards with EQuIS Enterprise;
• Using desktop and enterprise GIS software, including ArcMap, ArcGIS Pro, ArcGIS Server, ArcGIS Online, and open-source alternatives, to collect, store, analyze, and visualize spatial data;
• Fieldwork such as soil, surface water and groundwater sampling and remediation treatment system operation and maintenance; and
• Using mobile data collection platforms, such as EQuIS Collect, Survey123, Collector for ArcGIS, ArcGIS Field Maps, and GPS equipment for data collection while performing fieldwork.

Education and Licensure
• Bachelor's degree in geology or environmental, civil, or chemical engineering, Geosciences, GIS or Geography. (required)
• Advanced degree in the same. (preferred)

Skills, Experience and Qualifications
• Related work experience in a similar role. (preferred)
• Experience in environmental field sampling, chemistry, data analysis and/or visualization. (preferred)
• Programming skills with one of the programming languages such as Python, R, SQL, .NET, Java/JavaScript, and VBA. (required)
• Strong analytical and problem-solving skills. (required)
• Experience with the off-the-shelf environmental data management systems (EQuIS). (preferred)
• Experience with database technology such as Microsoft SQL Server and SQL Server Data Management Studio. (preferred)
• Knowledge of laboratory analytical data verification and validation processes. (preferred)
• Experience with enterprise database platforms and/or GIS software (ArcGIS). (preferred)
• Knowledge of data dashboard and BI tool development. (preferred)
• Academic training in environmentally-related disciplines, such as geology, civil/environmental engineering, water/natural resources, or environmental studies. (preferred)
• Field work and overnight travel. (required)
• Health & Safety training, medical monitoring, and client-driven drug and background testing. (required)
• Valid U.S. driver’s license and satisfactory driving record for business travel. (required)

description:
Job Summary

Provides customer analytics and performance reporting that drive business priorities for internal parners in Marketing and Brand Experience, Consumer, Community and Wholesale Banking lines of business. Designs and maintains customer and segment scorecards, dashboards and reports that offer visibility into our customer base. Develops and delivers customer behavioral analyses that answer critical business questions, validate assumptions and debunk myths. Works with customer household, account and transaction data to support, execute, and measure business strategies to drive revenue, improve customer experience, and reduce costs.

Job Duties and Responsibilities
• Performs data mining and customer analysis. Works with business partners to define issues and information needs and translates them into specific data/technical requirements to support business initiatives and projects.
• Researches, compiles, and performs complex analysis on critical customer, account, and transactional data using tools such as SQL Assistant, Databricks, Power BI, etc.
• Maintains necessary processes, controls and procedures to ensure data accuracy and integrity. Leverages multiple internal or external information sources and ensures adherence to data management/data governance regulations and policies.
• Remains current on best practices of business analytics trends, techniques and tools. May identify emerging trends in technology and analysis as opportunities for future business growth and development.
• Manages multiple assignments simultaneously and completes assignments within established time frames. Keeps all facts straight and communicates key points succinctly.
• Presents complex material to all levels of management in a digestible, consumable manner.
• May work closely with the analytics' data science team to identify location, structure, and function of data related to modeling projects. Tracks down programs, data sources and crafting queries to power programs.
• May be responsible for designing and developing data visualization solutions according to business requirements to effectively communicate insights and provide performance measurement solutions to business decision makers.
• May be a liaison between business units, technology teams, finance teams and other support teams.
• May develop content for communication strategies across multiple lines of business; develops and supports communication tools; creates engaging and informative presentations that communicate results to management and executive audiences.
• Each team member is expected to be aware of risk within their functional area. This includes observing all policies, procedures, laws, regulations and risk limits specific to their role. Additionally, they should raise and report known or suspected violations to the appropriate Company authority in a timely fashion.

Job Description

At Regions, the Risk Information Technology and Data Analyst is a key member of the Innovation and IT and Data Risk Management organization and performs activities consistent with the second line of defense. This position will influence enterprise innovation and conduct IT and Data risk identification, measurement, mitigation, monitoring, and reporting activities in accordance with the enterprise strategy and enterprise risk appetite.

Primary Responsibilities
• Assists in conducting key tasks and/or projects to perform IT and Data Risk Assessments, Advisory Reviews, Project Assessments, 3rd Party Testing, and other project reviews as identified across all aspects of Information Technology and Data, including application development, cyber security, enterprise architecture, business continuity and disaster recovery, data governance, data quality, and change management, etc.

• Monitors, tracks, and reports mitigation and resolution of IT and Data risk issues
• Develops and manages reporting to effectively communicate key risks, findings, and recommendations for improvement and discuss results with key stakeholders

This position is exempt from timekeeping requirements under the Fair Labor Standards Act and is not eligible for overtime pay.

description:
About Stripe Theory:

Stripe Theory is an agency made up of a team of data-driven digital marketers, communication professionals, and analysts. We call ourselves interpreters of data because that’s just what we do — use data to inform and fuel strategies across PR, marketing, and digital.

About ACC:

Stripe is an acquisition of ACC - Acceleration Community of Companies. ACC is an integrated team of cutting-edge media, marketing, and communications companies, offering best-in-class marketing solutions where strategy, technology, and creativity converge.

About the Role:

We are looking for a Senior Marketing Data Analyst who has a passion for all things marketing, is a great writer, and can uncover — and simplify — actionable insights for clients and stakeholders. As part of our team, you’ll be involved in a variety of client projects and work in a fast-paced, collaborative agency environment where no day is the same.

Responsibilities may include but are not limited to:
• Marketing data analysis and report writing that is actionable and easy to interpret for various clients.
• Identifying trends, conclusions, and strategic insights based on findings in the marketing data.
• Performing ROI analysis to evaluate the efficiency and effectiveness of different channels, ad formats, and campaigns.
• Presenting ongoing report deliverables to clients.
• Using Tableau to create tables, visualizations, and dashboards.
• Facilitating the automation of data pulls from a variety of platforms (social media, email, website analytics, CRM programs, e-commerce, and more).
• ​​Supporting client team leads on any internal projects to uplevel the analytics practice, including the implementation of analytical tools, techniques, processes, and frameworks.
• Coaching more junior members in best practices and troubleshooting data-related issues.
• Owning measurement aspects of new business pitches, renewals, and EOY audits, enabling strategies that are led by data and insights.
• Setting up data collection tools, including social listening and media monitoring.
• Staying up-to-date on analytics news and trends, and sharing these with the team.
• Supporting clients in quick crisis and issues reporting.
• Participating in team brainstorming sessions.

Qualifications:
• Bachelor’s degree in Advertising, Marketing, or equivalent.
• 3+ years of experience in a similar marketing strategist or marketing analytics role.
• 3+ years of experience writing marketing data insights and creating reports.
• 3+ years of experience in building tables, visualizations, and dashboards with a BI tool such as Tableau, Domo or similar
• Proficient in Excel, Google Sheets, or equivalent.
• Mastered understanding of social media platforms (Facebook, Twitter, LinkedIn, Instagram, YouTube, TikTok, Pinterest) as well as other marketing channels (website, email, organic search, digital advertising, CRM programs, e-commerce, traditional advertising).
• Strong verbal and written communication skills – whether presenting to colleagues, drafting emails to clients, or participating in brainstorming sessions.
• Demonstrated ability to multitask, prioritize, and manage deadlines.
• Strong research skills.
• Developed interpersonal skills and the ability to work effectively with a variety of people across multiple accounts.
• Eagerness to learn new tools and techniques.

Stripe Theory is an Equal Opportunity Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, age, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity / expression, national origin, protected veteran status, or any other characteristic protected under federal, state or local law, where applicable, and those with criminal histories will be considered in a manner consistent with applicable state and local laws

Note: Our team has a hybrid schedule between remote work and our Midtown Atlanta office.

About Stripe Theory

We are a digital marketing agency focused on growing brands through data, storytelling and strategy. We started Stripe Theory on the belief that a data-first, cross-trained and discipline-agnostic approach to marketing and strategy could deliver greater client value and innovation at a lower cost. At Stripe Theory, we embrace the chaos of marketing and use data to navigate the noise. This is how we operate at the cusp of what is next.

Job Title: Data Analyst (Mid)
Location: Huntsville
Job Category: Information Technology
Time Type: Full-time

Security Suitability: Must pass FBI security suitability
Polygraph Requirement: Must pass an FBI-administered Counterintelligence polygraph if one has not been conducted within the last five years.
Employee Type: W2 or 1099
Citizenship: US Citizen, no Dual Citizenship

Job Summary:
The Data Analyst (Mid) will be a vital member of the Service Operation team, working to enhance data management practices and ensure compliance with Executive Order 14028 and Memorandum 21-31. This role involves supporting the enrollment of enterprise IT assets into the centralized logging repository, developing schemas to standardize logs, and conducting independent validation and verification (IV&V) of consolidated logs. The Data Analyst will also assist in reviewing and approving secured external website access requests (EWARS), managing the Enterprise IT configuration Change Management process, and supporting the administration of accounts for Justice Enterprise File Sharing (JEFS).

Key Responsibilities:
· Analyze and interpret data related to enterprise IT asset enrollment in the centralized logging repository.
· Develop and maintain schemas to standardize the logs being ingested to ensure data integrity and security.
· Engage with system owners and stakeholders to facilitate the enrollment process and gather necessary data.
· Conduct independent validation and verification (IV&V) of consolidated logs to ensure compliance with standards and policies.
· Support the review and approval of secured external website access requests (EWARS) by analyzing relevant data.
· Collaborate with team members to oversee the Enterprise IT configuration Change Management process, ensuring proper documentation and compliance.
· Utilize data visualization tools (e.g., Power BI) to create reports and dashboards that present findings and recommendations.
· Participate in regular team meetings to discuss ongoing projects, provide updates, and receive feedback.

Unique Skills/Tasks/Software:
· Proficiency in Cybersecurity SIEM tools (e.g., Splunk, Elastic).
· Experience with Microsoft Power Platform applications, including Power BI, Power Apps, and Power Automate.
· Familiarity with Atlassian Software products (JIRA, Confluence, Service Desk) for project tracking and documentation.

Preferred Certifications:
· PMI Project Management Professional (PMP)
· Splunk Core Certified Power User
· ITIL v4 Practice Manager (PM)
· Microsoft Power BI Data Analyst Associate

Qualifications:
· Bachelor's degree in Data Science, Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field (or equivalent experience).
· Minimum 3 years of experience in data analysis, business analysis, or a related field.
· Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to work with complex datasets.
· Excellent communication skills for presenting findings and collaborating with stakeholders.
Knowledge of cybersecurity principles and practices is a plus.

title: Data Analyst Intern - Summer 2025

description:
Overview
Prepare to dive deep into data, optimize campaigns, and uncover the trends that will drive our marketing strategies for healthcare organizations around the country. We're looking for a Data Analyst who loves to analyze campaign performance data, develop data-driven narratives and provide actionable insights and recommendations in an agency setting. This role will play an important part to shape our rapidly evolving analytics practice, will build meaningful marketing models and will develop compelling data visualizations to complement our campaign efforts.
Ideal candidates will oversee measurement plan strategy, collection, analysis, and interpretation of media performance across multiple campaign channels and collaborate with cross-functional teams to deliver client-ready dashboards and reporting. Additionally, this role will guide new process and analytics capabilities, validate and maintain data integrity and train an extended team on leveraging predictive and prescriptive marketing data.
If you have a passion for data analysis and a drive to make a meaningful impact on the communities and clients we serve, we should talk.
Responsibilities
- Report on campaign performance and optimize channels through A/B testing, KPI strategy and tracking, customer segmentation, attribution modeling, and data modeling.
- Create actionable insights from complex data, and share compelling narratives with our performance marketing teams and clients to guide agile strategic recommendations and decisions.
- Develop dashboards and resources to uncover opportunities for improvement, and drive smarter, data-driven decisions.
- Foster an agile and data-driven mindset across the team by providing training, documentation, and support to improve understanding and engagement in campaign performances across clients.
- Develop standardized metrics and forecasts to evaluate and benchmark short- and long-term planning that will help shape effective strategies to better meet client needs.
- Assist in building out the agency's analytics services and demonstrate an ongoing commitment to innovation that establishes the agency as an innovative leader in healthcare marketing analytics.
- Design and conduct A/B testing and make recommendations for optimization
- Produce and maintain data models, own data product development and liaise with strategic partners for data maintenance.
- Develop subject matter expertise in data, measurement, ad tech, and targeting capabilities for select marketing channels, and support agency thought leadership and marketing by providing a strong point of view on trends, compliance changes, platform updates, and more related to analytics and measurement. Track campaign performance, audience segmentation, and revenue impact, and develop predictive models to forecast performance trends.
- Support agency marketing through identification of case study material.
- Collaborate with clients with diverse tech stacks to ensure we efficiently leverage investments they've made in advanced analytics platforms, CRM, call tracking tools, and more in our measurement plans.
Required Skills/Experience
- Bachelor's degree in statistics, data analytics, applied mathematics, or marketing.
- Minimum four years of agency experience in business intelligence, data analysis, or a similar role, with expertise in turning complex data into recommendations.
- Hands-on experience with data analytics tools like SQL, Python, R, or BigQuery.
- Expertise in data visualization tools (Tableau, PowerBI, Looker, etc.), and marketing analytics platforms (Google Analytics, Adobe Analytics).
- Fluency in MarTech tools like call tracking (Invoca, CallRail), CDP (Freshpaint, Segment), CRM (Salesforce), and others that may advance agency measurement offering
- Strong communication skills, with the ability to clean, manage, and analyze large datasets and transform them into actionable insights that resonate with stakeholders at all levels.
- Experience with data-based decision-making processes, with a passion for marketing performance analytics and optimization.
- Familiarity with CRM integration for downstream ROI analysis and previous experience in healthcare marketing and healthcare compliance a plus.
True North Custom provides strategic marketing solutions for hundreds of healthcare clients nationwide. Using custom content via digital, print, and online campaigns, we target audiences through data with strategic marketing messages designed to move healthcare consumers to action.
What We Offer
- Competitive compensation and benefits package inclusive of maternity/paternity leave
- 100% remote work
- Unlimited PTO and sick time
- A customer-centric culture that embraces excellence, urgency, diversity, creativity, and open communication
- A collaborative environment that fosters mutual respect and enhanced results
- Cultivation of each team member's talent and leadership abilities through continuing education and a commitment to offering opportunities for internal career growth. We encourage and embrace new ideas and perspectives from every member of our team.
This position may be performed remotely anywhere within the United States while accommodating Eastern time company office hours.

description:
The Hiller Companies, LLC has an immediate opening for a Sr. Data Analyst.

Hiller offers fire protection and life safety products and services that are preserving lives and property all around the world. Headquartered in Mobile, Alabama, Hiller extends its reach globally as well as in domestic markets with offices across the United States. For more than 100 years, we have been laser-focused on one goal making the world a safer place. We are proud to be on the forefront of technology and innovation by creating adaptable safety solutions. As we continue to grow and expand our life safety footprint, we pledge to keep our customers top of mind while striving to design, install and service the most compliant, reliable systems available.

Job Summary: The Sr Data Analyst supports Hillers evolution towards digitization and data driven culture. In this role you will be the data workstream lead on the Data & Analytics (D&A) team responsible for implementing the data & analytics vision. This workstream is critical in creating, governing, and enhancing dozens of data assets that drive thousands of downstream decisions at Hiller, including modernizing and maintaining our data governance program.

This position will ideally be located in Phoenix, AZ area, with hybrid work scheduling. We will consider other remote candidates, who are able to work hybrid in another Hiller office location.

Job Responsibilities:
• Support the creation and enhancements of all needed Master Data Assets
• Lead the implementation of Hillers Data Governance Program
• Conduct continuous improvement of Master Data Asset backend queries and data pipelines
• Lead Data Clean Up Exercises and Historical Restatements of Master Data Assets

What We Are Looking For:
• Bachelors degree or higher in computer science, data science, statistics, or a related field
• 6+ years of experience with hand on data exploration, data cleaning, data analysis, and data mining
• 6+ years experience in data governance
• 6+ years of experience analyzing structured and unstructured data sources
• 3+ years of experience with statistical and general-purpose programming languages for data analysis practices
• Experience developing predictive data models, quantitative analyses and visualization of targeted data sources
• Experience leading projects and deliverables
• Experience in presenting to leadership to get guidance and propose business cases
• Exceptional communication and presentation skills, with the ability to convey complex ideas in a clear and concise manner
• Experience leading the development of solutions to complex programs
• Experienced with the following programming languages: Python, R, SQL, DAX, Python and relevant libraries like Pandas, PyTorch, Tensorflow, etc.
• Prefer candidates with experience in using data governance tools such as Talend or Informatica
• Data architecture expertise for CoPilot deployments preferred
• Working with APIs and Data engineering concepts a plus
• Prefer candidates with the demonstrated ability to design, develop, and deploy advanced analytics solutions and end-to-end data-driven solutions in the construction industry.

Hiller is a drug-free workplace, an equal opportunity employer and ADA compliant.

We are proud to operate according to our Core Values: Passion to Perform, Trust to Act, Act Responsibly and Make It Fun.

Most employee benefits start from the first day of employment, including:
• Competitive compensation package, including pay advancement opportunities for industry certifications and continuing education
• Comprehensive benefits package, including health, dental & vision insurance, retirement plans, company paid & voluntary life insurance, company paid short-term disability, voluntary long-term disability, critical illness & accident insurance and paid time off
• Company-provided training, tools and equipment, including $150 annual boot allowance for employees required to wear safety boots in their jobs
• Career advancement potential within a growing company.

Join us in our mission to provide comprehensive fire protection solutions and peace of mind to our customers and together let's make the world a safer place.
